{"id":"orch-go-00iw3","title":"Synthesize headless investigations (15)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **headless** has accumulated 15 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-20-inv-implement-headless-spawn-mode-add.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-make-headless-mode-default-deprecate.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-scope-out-headless-swarm-implementation.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-headless-spawn-not-sending-prompts.md\n- 2025-12-22-debug-headless-spawns-not-discoverable-by-beads-id.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-headless-spawn-mode-readiness-what.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-headless-spawn-registers-wrong-project.md\n- 2025-12-23-debug-headless-spawn-model-format.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-headless-spawn-does-not-pass.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-orch-status-shows-headless-agents.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-token-limit-explosion-headless-spawn.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-test-headless-mode.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-test-headless-spawn-list-files.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-test-headless-spawn.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-test-headless-spawn-after-fix.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-20 [INV] Legacy Artifacts Synthesis Protocol Alignment\n2025-12-20 [INV] Enhance status command with swarm progress\n2025-12-20 [INV] Fix Spawn to Use Standalone Mode with TUI\n2025-12-20 [INV] Implement Headless Spawn Mode\n2025-12-20 [INV] Make Headless Mode Default for Spawn\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"headless\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-06T18:35:51.614164-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T19:56:44.902708-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T19:56:44.902708-08:00","close_reason":"Duplicate synthesis issue","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-00n","title":"orch-go: Add agent registry for persistent tracking","description":"Port Python's AgentRegistry (~/.orch/registry.json) to Go. Foundation for clean, abandon, wait, status --global. Without this, orch-go is stateless.","notes":"workspace: .orch/workspace/og-feat-orch-add-agent-20dec","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-20T10:11:46.639815-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-20T10:24:54.456349-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-20T10:24:54.456349-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-00zsx","title":"Add ListReadyIssuesForProject() to issue_adapter.go","description":"## Context\n\nPart of cross-project daemon implementation. See parent investigation:\n`.kb/investigations/2026-01-21-inv-cross-project-daemon-poll-multiple.md`\n\nDepends on: orch-go-mdoob (project discovery)\n\n## Task\n\nAdd project-aware issue listing function to `pkg/daemon/issue_adapter.go`.\n\n## Implementation\n\n```go\n// ListReadyIssuesForProject returns triage:ready issues for a specific project\nfunc ListReadyIssuesForProject(projectPath string) ([]beads.Issue, error) {\n    // 1. Use beads.FindSocketPath(projectPath) instead of \"\"\n    // 2. Or use CLI fallback with: bd ready --json --limit 0 --db \u003cprojectPath\u003e/.beads/beads.db\n    // 3. Return issues with project context attached\n}\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Function accepts projectPath and returns issues from that project\n- [ ] Works with both RPC and CLI fallback modes\n- [ ] Error in one project doesn't crash - returns empty list with logged warning\n- [ ] Unit test verifying project targeting","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-21T20:27:09.200232472Z","updated_at":"2026-01-21T20:43:19.957308722Z","closed_at":"2026-01-21T20:43:19.957308722Z","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - ListReadyIssuesForProject() implemented. Tests pass.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-02mni","title":"Add question entity type to beads","description":"Add 'question' as new beads entity type with minimal schema.\n\nSchema: id, title, description, status, priority, labels, created_at, updated_at, closed_at, close_reason\nOmit: assignee, estimate, repro, understanding (not applicable to questions)\nStatus values: open, investigating, answered, closed\n\nCLI: bd create --type question --title 'Should we...'\n\nParent epic: orch-go-5j2hx","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-18T11:49:19.892323-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-18T12:50:17.502576-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-18T12:50:17.502576-08:00","close_reason":"Completed in beads repo. Commits: 2dc8f7dc (question type), d14cf911 (lifecycle), 744af9cf (gates)"}
