{"id":"orch-go-0dqjb","title":"Update session-resume-protocol.md to clarify 'interactive sessions only'","description":"Architect recommendation (orch-go-lvrzc): Update .kb/guides/session-resume-protocol.md to explicitly state this guide covers INTERACTIVE orchestrator sessions ('orch session start/end'), NOT spawned orchestrator agents ('orch spawn orchestrator'). Add comparison note explaining the distinction. Reference: .kb/investigations/2026-01-13-inv-analyze-orchestrator-session-management-architecture.md.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-13T12:32:38.079338-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-13T13:04:11.312133-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-13T13:04:11.312133-08:00","close_reason":"Updated session-resume-protocol.md with explicit orchestrator-only scope. Added scope statement, contrast table, and qualified all ambiguous 'session' references (15+ instances). Investigation and SYNTHESIS.md committed."}
{"id":"orch-go-0ez8w","title":"Synthesize beads investigations (18)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **beads** has accumulated 18 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-19-inv-set-beads-issue-status-progress.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-scaffold-beads-ui-v2-bun.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-beads-kb-workspace-relationships-how.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-beads-oss-relationship-fork-vs.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-orch-complete-closes-beads-issue.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-beads-multi-repo-hydration-why.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-add-beads-stats-dashboard-stats.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-add-fallback-beads-close-reason.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-beads-database-pollution-orch-go.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-design-beads-integration-strategy-orch.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-implement-pkg-beads-go-rpc.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-implement-pkg-beads-rpc-client.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-fix-short-beads-id-resolution.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-recover-priority-beads-deduplication-abstraction.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-fix-beads-type-field-showing.md\n- 2026-01-07-inv-consider-auto-starting-beads-daemon.md\n- 2026-01-04-debug-orch-review-timeout-beads-api.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-remove-beads-tracking-orchestrator-meta.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch complete Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch spawn Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] Set beads issue status to in_progress on spawn\n2025-12-19 [INV] Update README with current CLI commands and usage\n2025-12-19 [INV] Fix comment ID parsing - Comment.ID type mismatch\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"beads\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T19:11:32.698715-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T22:47:03.431352-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T22:47:03.431352-08:00","close_reason":"Bulk close: kb reflect synthesis noise","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0g1pi","title":"Daemon doesn't see newly created issues with triage:ready label","description":"**Observed:**\n- Created pw-ww8p in price-watch with triage:ready label\n- Verified label exists in local DB and JSONL file\n- Daemon polls price-watch but pw-ww8p doesn't appear in skip list or spawn list\n- Other pw-* issues from same project DO appear\n- Restarting daemon didn't help\n- orch daemon preview DOES show the issue as spawnable\n\n**Suspected cause:**\n- Daemon may be caching issue list\n- Or reading from different file location than bd export writes to\n- Or some race condition in JSONL parsing\n\n**Workaround:** Manual spawn with --bypass-triage works","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-22T09:46:40.205192-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-22T21:39:12.321085-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-22T21:39:12.321085-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Fixed daemon to iterate through all candidate issues when session dedup or Phase: Complete check fails. Previously, failing check on highest-priority issue caused daemon to stop looking. Commit: 8c57d712. Tests written but couldn't run in sandbox (no go binary). Reproduction verified via code analysis: Error=nil was breaking retry logic in caller."}
