{"id":"orch-go-0iim","title":"Add outputs.required to artifact-producing skills","description":"## Problem\n\nOnly `investigation` skill has `outputs.required` defined. Other artifact-producing skills have no verification gates.\n\n## Skills to Update\n\n| Skill | Artifact Pattern | Structure Checks |\n|-------|------------------|------------------|\n| systematic-debugging | `.kb/investigations/{date}-*debug*.md` | D.E.K.N., self-review |\n| reliability-testing | `.kb/investigations/{date}-*reliability*.md` | D.E.K.N., go/no-go section |\n| research | `.kb/investigations/{date}-*research*.md` | D.E.K.N., recommendation section |\n| architect | `.kb/decisions/{date}-*.md` OR `.kb/investigations/{date}-*.md` | D.E.K.N. |\n| codebase-audit | `.kb/investigations/{date}-*audit*.md` | D.E.K.N., findings section |\n\n## Implementation\n\nAdd to each skill's `.skillc/skill.yaml`:\n\n```yaml\noutputs:\n  required:\n    - pattern: \".kb/investigations/{date}-*[pattern]*.md\"\n      description: \"[Skill] file with findings\"\n  optional:\n    - pattern: \".kb/decisions/{date}-*.md\"\n      description: \"Promoted decision (if recommendation accepted)\"\n```\n\n## Not Covered (different verification needed)\n\n- **feature-impl** - Output is commits, not files\n- **issue-creation** - Output is beads issue\n- **design-session** - Output varies (epic/investigation/decision)\n- **kb-reflect** - Output is kb actions\n\nThese need verification in `orch complete`, not `skillc verify`.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] systematic-debugging has outputs.required\n- [ ] reliability-testing has outputs.required  \n- [ ] research has outputs.required\n- [ ] architect has outputs.required\n- [ ] codebase-audit has outputs.required\n- [ ] All skills rebuild with `skillc build`\n- [ ] `skillc verify` works on each skill","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T09:47:19.219826-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T18:27:32.687223-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T18:27:32.687223-08:00","close_reason":"Added outputs.required to 4 artifact-producing skills (codebase-audit, architect, research, reliability-testing). All verify tests pass. Committed to ~/.claude/skills and orch-go.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0iped","title":"Implement skill size reduction and compact output flags","description":"Investigation: 2026-01-16-inv-analyze-orchestration-session-hit-context.md\n\nContext: Orchestration sessions hit context limits prematurely because 67% of context consumed by setup (orchestrator skill = 2,385 lines, ~28K tokens).\n\nRecommendation: Create 'core' (500-800 lines) and 'reference' (2,385 lines) skill variants. Add --compact flag to orch status (show only running/recent agents, not all 182).\n\nKey insight: Skill content + tool output must fit within context budget alongside actual work.\n\nEvidence: Session consumed 56K tokens before work began - skill embedding alone was ~50% of setup context.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-18T01:55:44.665202-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-18T01:55:44.665202-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-0is4k","title":"Orchestrators should know registered projects via kb projects list","description":"## Problem\n\nMeta-orchestrators and orchestrators don't know where orch-managed projects are. When asked to spawn work in another project (e.g., price-watch), they have to search for paths.\n\n## Solution\n\nInclude `kb projects list` output (or summary) in orchestrator context so they know:\n- What projects exist\n- Where they're located\n- Can spawn cross-project work without path hunting\n\n## Evidence\n\nMeta-orchestrator couldn't find price-watch path until running `kb projects list`.\n\n## Implementation Options\n\n1. Add to ORCHESTRATOR_CONTEXT.md template\n2. Add to meta-orchestrator skill context\n3. Create `orch projects` command that wraps kb projects list","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-06T09:31:32.769909-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T09:46:01.080693-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T09:46:01.080693-08:00","close_reason":"(light tier - no synthesis by design)","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0j68e","title":"Synthesize skill investigations (17)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **skill** has accumulated 17 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-20-inv-update-investigation-skill-use-summary.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-de-bloat-feature-impl-skill.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-migrate-feature-impl-skill-skillc.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-pilot-migration-convert-investigation-skill.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-audit-recent-skill-changes-their.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-create-kb-reflect-skill-triaging.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-fix-skill-constraint-scoping-currently.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-implement-skill-constraint-verification-orch.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-enhance-kb-reflect-skill-propose.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-extend-skill-yaml-schema-spawn.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-add-skill-change-taxonomy-decision.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-skill-change-taxonomy.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-phase-skill-type-detection-spawn.md\n- 2026-01-05-design-claude-design-skill-evaluation.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-design-principles-skill-integration-skill.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-diagnose-investigation-skill-29-completion.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-diagnose-investigation-skill-32-completion.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch spawn Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] Set beads issue status to in_progress on spawn\n2025-12-19 [INV] Update README with current CLI commands and usage\n2025-12-19 [INV] say hello and exit immediately\n2025-12-20 [INV] Legacy Artifacts Synthesis Protocol Alignment\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"skill\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-08T11:11:03.956425-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T14:58:14.594106-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T14:58:14.594106-08:00","close_reason":"Duplicate synthesis issue","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0j92g","title":"--max-agents 0 flag doesn't disable concurrency limit","description":"The flag treats 0 as 'not set' and falls through to default. Workaround: ORCH_MAX_AGENTS=0 env var. Fix: distinguish 'not set' from 'explicitly 0'.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-20T13:24:21.133979-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-22T11:23:52.345677-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-22T11:23:52.345677-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/... -run TestGetMaxAgents - 6 passed, 0 failed. Root cause: flag default 0 conflicted with 'unlimited' value. Fix: use -1 as sentinel for 'not set'. Also added two new tests verifying --max-agents 0 and ORCH_MAX_AGENTS=0 both return 0 (unlimited)."}
{"id":"orch-go-0jtbr","title":"Synthesize status investigations (12)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **status** has accumulated 12 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-20-inv-enhance-status-command-swarm-progress.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-investigate-orch-status-showing-stale.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-orch-status-showing-stale-sessions.md\n- 2025-12-22-debug-orch-status-stale-sessions.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-update-orch-status-use-islive.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-orch-status-can-detect-active.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-orch-status-shows-active-agents.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-orch-status-takes-11-seconds.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-fix-status-filter-test-expects.md\n- 2026-01-05-debug-fix-orch-status-showing-different.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-orch-status-shows-completed-agents.md\n- 2026-01-07-inv-orch-status-surface-drift-metrics.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch complete Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch spawn Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Orch Status Command\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Project Scaffolding and Build Setup\n2025-12-19 [INV] OpenCode Client Package Session Management\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"status\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:08.025964-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:41.665435-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:41.665435-08:00","close_reason":"Bulk close: kb reflect synthesis issues are noise until detection is fixed","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0k0a","title":"Auto-switch accounts before hitting rate limits","description":"Before orch spawn, check current account usage. If 5-hour session \u003e80% OR weekly \u003e90%, auto-switch to alternate account (if available and has capacity). Prevents friction from hitting limits mid-work. Should check both accounts and pick the one with most headroom.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-24T09:05:49.042308-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-24T09:12:40.481796-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-24T09:12:40.481796-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented auto-account-switching with configurable thresholds (5h \u003e80%, weekly \u003e90%). Switches to alternate account with better headroom before spawn. All tests pass, committed as 6f9539c.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0kkz","title":"Add --workdir flag to orch tail for cross-project agent tailing","description":"**Symptom:** Cannot tail cross-project agents - `orch tail pw-6j8t` fails with 'no agent found' because it only checks current project.\n\n**Expected:** `orch tail pw-6j8t --workdir /path/to/price-watch` should work like other cross-project commands.\n\n**Related:** Similar to --workdir support in orch complete. Need to pass x-opencode-directory header when querying OpenCode API for session messages.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-29T11:08:05.084602-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T12:12:29.205567-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T12:12:29.205567-08:00","close_reason":"Added --workdir flag to orch tail for cross-project agent tailing. Flag uses target project directory for workspace search and OpenCode API x-opencode-directory header. Includes helpful error messages suggesting --workdir when issue ID appears to belong to different project."}
{"id":"orch-go-0l1d","title":"Dashboard: Debounce gold 'processing' border on agent cards","description":"UX issue: Gold processing border toggles rapidly on/off as agent switches between active tool calls and waiting. Visually distracting. Fix: Debounce the 'processing' state - stay gold for 5-10 seconds after last activity before transitioning to idle appearance. Could also add CSS transition for smoother visual change.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-26T16:36:55.420672-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T16:45:59.862316-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T16:45:59.862316-08:00","close_reason":"Debounced gold processing border from 1s to 5s delay, added 500ms CSS transitions for smooth fades. Removed animate-pulse (solid gold sufficient). Commit: de002c60. Leave it Better: kn-a9e5ef.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0l2f9","title":"Add orch doctor --sessions for workspace/session cross-reference","description":"## Problem\nNo way to detect:\n- Workspaces whose sessions were garbage-collected\n- Sessions without corresponding workspaces\n- Zombie sessions that appear active but are stuck\n\n## Impact\nNo systematic cleanup or zombie detection.\n\n## Solution\nAdd `orch doctor --sessions` that cross-references:\n1. Workspaces in `.orch/workspace/` with their `.session_id` files\n2. Active sessions from OpenCode API (`GET /session`)\n3. Registry entries in `~/.orch/registry.json`\n\n## Output\n```\norch doctor --sessions\nWorkspaces: 288\nSessions: 15 active\nOrphaned workspaces: 3 (session deleted)\nOrphaned sessions: 1 (no workspace)\nZombie sessions: 0\n```\n\n## References\n- Investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-06-inv-workspace-session-architecture.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-06T10:28:34.492457-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T17:52:26.136859-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T17:52:26.136859-08:00","close_reason":"Enhanced orch doctor --sessions to cross-reference workspaces, OpenCode sessions, and registry with zombie detection. Output matches spec. All tests passing."}
{"id":"orch-go-0n4ud","title":"Fix tmux socket path for orch serve running inside overmind","description":"**Problem:** Dashboard context API and follow mode fail because orch serve connects to wrong tmux server.\n\n**Root cause:** Overmind runs services inside its own tmux server with socket at /var/folders/.../overmind-orch-go-*. When orch serve runs tmux commands without specifying socket, it connects to overmind's tmux (no orchestrator session) instead of main tmux at /tmp/tmux-501/default.\n\n**Evidence:**\n- `tmux display-message -t orchestrator -p '#{window_index}'` works from shell (main tmux)\n- Same command fails from orch serve (overmind's tmux)\n- Two tmux servers visible in `ps aux | grep tmux`\n\n**Solution:** Add `-S /tmp/tmux-$(id -u)/default` to tmux commands in pkg/tmux/tmux.go, or detect the correct socket path.\n\n**Affected functionality:**\n- /api/context endpoint\n- Dashboard 'Follow Orchestrator' mode  \n- Tmux auto-switch (sync-workers-session.sh works because it runs from shell)\n\n**Location:** pkg/tmux/tmux.go - tmuxCommand() and findTmux() functions","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-15T13:25:05.452879-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-15T13:34:32.819262-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-15T13:34:32.819262-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Fixed Dashboard /api/context by detecting main tmux socket when running inside overmind. Tests: go test ./pkg/tmux/... - all passing. API endpoint verified returning orchestrator cwd.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0nga","title":"Real-time agent activity display in dashboard","description":"Dashboard should show live agent activity for headless spawns:\n1. Filter active vs completed sessions (currently shows stale sessions)\n2. Show current activity per agent (last message, current tool, tokens)\n3. Live updates via SSE as agents work\n\nCurrent gap: /api/agents returns all sessions including completed ones from days ago. Need to detect which sessions are actively running vs idle/completed.\n\nRelated: orch-go-36b (dashboard visibility investigation)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-22T21:02:43.514269-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T21:19:16.656863-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T21:19:16.656863-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented real-time agent activity display with live SSE updates. Added activity tracking to agent cards, message.part event parsing, Active Only filter, and granular store updates. All code committed and builds successfully."}
{"id":"orch-go-0ns2e","title":"Evaluate GUPP-style hooks for worker durability","description":"## Context\nGastown uses GUPP (Gastown Universal Propulsion Principle) hooks - persistent work assignment beads that survive session death. If an agent crashes mid-task, the next session picks up from the hook.\n\n## Problem\nCurrently if an orch-go worker dies mid-task, SPAWN_CONTEXT.md may not capture in-progress state. Work can be lost or require manual recovery.\n\n## Investigation Scope\n1. How does GUPP hook mechanism work in detail? (internal/cmd/hook.go)\n2. Could we implement hook-status beads without adopting persistent agent identities?\n3. What's the right granularity - per-spawn or per-phase?\n4. Does this conflict with our ephemeral agent philosophy?\n\n## Reference\n- Gastown investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-23-inv-gastown-orchestration-system-analysis-compare.md\n- Gastown gap analysis: gastown/.orch/workspace/ga-inv-gastown-gap-analysis-23jan-d2f0/investigation.md\n- GUPP in Gastown: templates/polecat-CLAUDE.md:100-118","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-23T19:11:34.335034-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-23T19:11:34.335034-08:00"}
