{"id":"orch-go-0r0m","title":"orch complete fails for orchestrator sessions - beads lookup before workspace detection","description":"orch complete for orchestrator sessions (which don't have beads tracking) tries beads lookup first, failing before it can detect the workspace is an orchestrator session.\n\nThe complete flow should:\n1. Check if workspace exists and has ORCHESTRATOR_CONTEXT.md or .tier=orchestrator\n2. If orchestrator session, use registry/workspace-based completion\n3. Only fall back to beads lookup for worker sessions\n\nCurrent behavior: beads lookup first, fails for orchestrator sessions.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-05T11:40:59.866635-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-05T15:20:40.47356-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-05T15:20:40.47356-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed orch complete for orchestrator sessions by adding registry-first lookup. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/ - 69.965s, all pass. Verified cross-project orchestrator completion works."}
