{"id":"orch-go-0r7w","title":"feat-037: Show orchestrator sessions in orch status","description":"Add orchestrator sessions from registry to orch status output.\n\n## Context\nDecision 2026-01-05-orchestrator-lifecycle-without-beads.md establishes session registry for orchestrators. Status command needs to show these alongside worker agents.\n\n## Implementation\n- In cmd/orch/status_cmd.go\n- Read from session registry (feat-035)\n- Display orchestrator sessions in a separate section or with distinct indicator\n- Show: workspace name, goal, duration, project\n\n## Display Format (suggested)\n```\nORCHESTRATOR SESSIONS\n  WORKSPACE                          GOAL                    DURATION  PROJECT\n  og-orch-ship-feature-05jan         Ship the feature        2h 15m    orch-go\n  meta-work-review-patterns-05jan    Review patterns         45m       -\n\nAGENTS\n  BEADS ID    STATUS    PHASE      ...\n```\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Active orchestrator sessions shown in status\n- Distinct from worker agents (different section or indicator)\n- Shows useful info: workspace, goal, duration\n- Empty state handled gracefully\n\n## Dependencies\n- feat-035 (session registry) must be implemented first\n\n## References\n- Decision: .kb/decisions/2026-01-05-orchestrator-lifecycle-without-beads.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-05T11:04:44.347932-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-05T11:35:32.784812-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-05T11:35:32.784812-08:00","close_reason":"Added ORCHESTRATOR SESSIONS section to orch status output. Shows workspace, goal, duration, and project from session registry. Supports --project filtering, adaptive terminal formatting (wide/narrow/card), and --json output. Empty state handled gracefully.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:daemon"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0rl18","title":"Synthesize tmux investigations (12)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **tmux** has accumulated 12 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-20-inv-migrate-orch-go-tmux-http.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-tmux-concurrent-delta.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-tmux-concurrent-epsilon.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-tmux-concurrent-zeta.md\n- 2025-12-21-debug-orch-send-fails-silently-tmux.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-add-tmux-fallback-orch-status.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-add-tmux-flag-orch-spawn.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-implement-attach-mode-tmux-spawn.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-tmux-spawn-killed.md\n- 2025-12-22-debug-orch-send-fails-silently-tmux.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-tmux-session-naming-confusing-hard.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-test-tmux-spawn.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch complete Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] Set beads issue status to in_progress on spawn\n2025-12-19 [INV] say hello and exit immediately\n2025-12-20 [INV] Add Abandon Command to orch-go\n2025-12-20 [INV] orch-go Add Question Command\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"tmux\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-08T10:10:45.209237-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T10:10:56.470065-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T10:10:56.470065-08:00","close_reason":"Synthesis is orchestrator work, not spawnable. Auto-creation disabled per decision 2026-01-07-synthesis-is-strategic-orchestrator-work.md","labels":["triage:review"]}
