{"id":"orch-go-0wxg","title":"kb reflect --create-issue needs deduplication","description":"If kb reflect --create-issue runs twice, it may create duplicate beads issues for the same topic.\n\nNeed to check if a synthesis issue already exists before creating:\n- Search for open issues with title matching 'Synthesize {topic} investigations'\n- Or add metadata/label to track (e.g., label: kb-reflect-synthesis)\n- Skip creation if issue already exists and is open\n\nThis is P1 because without it, automated kb reflect runs will spam duplicate issues.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-31T18:13:54.070469-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-31T18:25:21.094449-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-31T18:25:21.094449-08:00","close_reason":"Added deduplication to kb reflect --create-issue. The synthesisIssueExists() function queries bd list --status open --title-contains before creating issues. All tests pass. Commit: a6df795"}
{"id":"orch-go-0x12","title":"Add OpenCode launchd plist for auto-start and KeepAlive","description":"OpenCode serve is the foundation that orch daemon and orch serve depend on, but it has no auto-start mechanism.\n\nCurrent state:\n- com.orch.daemon.plist exists (orch daemon run)\n- com.orch-go.serve.plist exists (orch serve)  \n- NO opencode launchd plist - manual start required\n\nProblem: When OpenCode crashes or returns errors (like 'redirected too many times'), the entire orchestration system stalls. Daemon can't spawn, orch serve can't query sessions.\n\nDeliverable:\n1. Create ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.opencode.serve.plist\n   - ProgramArguments: opencode serve --port 4096\n   - RunAtLoad: true\n   - KeepAlive: true (restart on crash)\n   - StandardOutPath: ~/.orch/logs/opencode.log\n   - StandardErrorPath: ~/.orch/logs/opencode.err\n   - EnvironmentVariables: PATH with node/bun locations\n\n2. Test: launchctl bootstrap, verify auto-restart on kill\n\n3. Document in orchestrator skill under 'System Maintenance'\n\nReference: ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.orch.daemon.plist for pattern","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-26T11:49:15.938705-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T11:50:52.17382-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T11:50:52.17382-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented directly: Created ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.opencode.serve.plist with RunAtLoad and KeepAlive. Verified auto-restart works.","labels":["P1","skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0xa3v","title":"Self-Healing: Implement Phase 3 - Real-time Health Injection","description":"Implement real-time context injection of health signals (tool failures, context usage) into active agents using the noReply pattern, completing the Pain-as-Signal loop.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-17T02:23:19.082618-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T09:48:29.002864-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T09:48:29.002864-08:00","close_reason":"Closed"}
{"id":"orch-go-0xc1","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Investigate 'dead' agents in dashboard - agents...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-31T18:26:37.491449-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-01T03:28:22.230292-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-01T03:28:22.230292-08:00","close_reason":"Investigated dead agents lifecycle gap. Found two-system design (OpenCode sessions vs beads issues) is intentional. Dead agents occur when sessions go stale while issues remain in_progress. Discovered visibility gap: in_progress issues with NO session are invisible to dashboard. Recommended adding quick action buttons for dead agents. See .kb/investigations/2025-12-31-inv-investigate-dead-agents-dashboard-agents.md"}
{"id":"orch-go-0xl7e","title":"Synthesize cli investigations (17)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **cli** has accumulated 17 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-19-inv-cli-orch-complete-command.md\n- 2025-12-19-inv-cli-orch-spawn-command.md\n- 2025-12-19-inv-cli-orch-status-command.md\n- 2025-12-19-inv-cli-project-scaffolding-build.md\n- 2025-12-19-inv-update-readme-current-cli-commands.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-add-cli-commands-focus-drift.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-compare-orch-cli-python-orch.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-trace-evolution-orch-cli-python.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-cli-output-not-appearing-orch.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-cli-output-not-appearing.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-auto-detect-cli-commands-needing.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-auto-detect-new-cli-commands.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-evaluate-snap-cli-integration-visual.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-add-cli-commands-glass-orchestrator.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-recover-priority-cli-commands-reconcile.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-implement-orch-hotspot-cli-command.md\n- 2026-01-07-design-bd-cli-slow-launchd-env.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch complete Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch spawn Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Orch Status Command\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Project Scaffolding and Build Setup\n2025-12-19 [INV] OpenCode Client Package Session Management\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"cli\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:06.919377-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:42.445791-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:42.445791-08:00","close_reason":"Bulk close: kb reflect synthesis issues are noise until detection is fixed","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0xra","title":"Empty investigation templates created by agents that die early","description":"**Problem:** Found 5 empty investigation template files from agents that died in Planning phase. Pollutes .kb/investigations/.\n\n**Evidence this session:** Had to manually delete:\n- 2026-01-01-inv-glass-add-hover-capability-investigate.md\n- 2026-01-01-inv-glass-form-state-clears-clicking.md\n- 2026-01-01-inv-investigation-signals-predict-surfaced-work.md\n- 2026-01-01-inv-kb-reflect-auto-create-synthesis.md\n- 2026-01-01-inv-strengthen-verifysynthesis-validate-content-against.md\n- 2026-01-01-inv-dashboard-add-token-usage-stats.md\n\n**Root cause:** Agents create investigation file first (good for resume), but die before filling it. Template file remains.\n\n**Possible solutions:**\n1. Don't create investigation file until first finding is recorded\n2. Add cleanup command: kb prune --empty\n3. orch complete could detect and offer to delete empty artifacts\n4. Investigation skill: delay file creation until after Planning phase\n\n**Impact:** Manual cleanup needed; stale files confuse future agents searching for prior work.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-01T14:39:26.546809-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T20:23:47.562477-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T20:23:47.562477-08:00","close_reason":"orch clean --investigations: archives empty templates to .kb/investigations/archived/","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0ydvu","title":"Phase 1: Service monitoring daemon with crash notifications","description":"Background goroutine in orch serve that polls overmind status every 10s, tracks PIDs to detect crashes, and emits desktop notifications. Solves silent service failures (e.g., opencode crash discovered only when orch status fails). Implementation follows architecture from orch-go-e79ao. Success criteria: kill service process → notification within 15s, CPU overhead \u003c0.5%. See .orch/workspace/og-arch-design-observability-infrastructure-09jan-3e5e/SYNTHESIS.md for full design.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-09T18:32:20.269286-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-09T23:05:51.90187-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-09T23:05:51.90187-08:00","close_reason":"Service monitoring daemon implemented and validated. Detects crashes in 2-3s (target 15s), auto-restarts services, logs events to events.jsonl, CPU overhead 0.0% (target \u003c0.5%). Evidence: opencode crashed twice and auto-restarted successfully. Code committed in 9f249e88. Agent stuck at completion phase - orchestrator validated manually."}
{"id":"orch-go-0yox","title":"Dashboard shows 'Waiting for activity' - OpenCode API returns 0 messages despite messages existing on disk","description":"Dashboard SSE shows 'Waiting for activity...' for active agents. Investigation: Session ses_48fb59faeffe has 27 message files in ~/.local/share/opencode/storage/message/ses_48fb59faeffe*/ but curl to http://localhost:4096/session/ses_48fb59faeffe returns messages:0. The session.json file also shows messages:0. OpenCode stores messages in a separate directory from session metadata, and the API may not be loading them correctly. This breaks dashboard real-time activity display.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-30T09:27:59.253085-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-30T09:40:42.260541-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-30T09:40:42.260541-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed by adding last_activity to /api/agents response - dashboard now shows activity on initial load"}
{"id":"orch-go-0z5i4","title":"Implement Claude mode spawn (tmux + claude CLI)","description":"Create pkg/spawn/claude.go with tmux spawn implementation. Launch claude CLI in tmux window, write SPAWN_CONTEXT to file, monitor via tmux capture-pane.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T11:55:40.044688-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-09T12:20:15.968143-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-09T12:20:15.968143-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented Claude mode spawn in pkg/spawn/claude.go and integrated it into the spawn command. Agents can now be spawned via Claude Code CLI in tmux windows using a file-based context approach."}
