{"id":"orch-go-1kk2u","title":"Define workspace cleanup strategy","description":"## Context\nInvestigation (.kb/investigations/2026-01-06-inv-workspace-session-architecture.md) found that 'orphaned workspaces' was a misunderstanding of the tier system:\n- Light-tier workers (218 of 288) don't produce SYNTHESIS.md by design\n- Only ~10 workspaces were actually incomplete\n\n## Actual Need\nDefine a cleanup strategy for:\n1. Completed workspaces (archive after X days?)\n2. OpenCode sessions that accumulate indefinitely\n3. Workspace ↔ session cross-reference for detecting zombies\n\n## Scope\n- Policy decision on retention period\n- Implement orch clean --stale or similar\n- Add orch doctor --sessions for cross-reference","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-06T09:56:31.233338-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T11:58:12.405165-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T11:58:12.405165-08:00","close_reason":"(light tier - no synthesis by design)","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-1l7qy","title":"Daemon blocks child tasks when parent epic is in_progress","description":"## Problem\n\nChild tasks with `triage:ready` label are blocked by daemon when their parent epic is `in_progress`. This is backwards - `in_progress` parent should **unblock** children, not block them.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\n- Parent `open` → children blocked (epic not started)\n- Parent `in_progress` → children **unblocked** (epic is active, work should proceed)\n- Parent `closed` → children unblocked (or auto-closed?)\n\n## Workaround\n\nRemove parent relationship: `bd update pw-xxxx.1 --parent \"\"`\n\n## Context\n\nDiscovered in price-watch project when creating epic pw-u8th with 4 child tasks. All tasks had `triage:ready` but daemon wouldn't pick them up until parent relationship was removed.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-06T11:53:00.758289-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T13:09:15.324698-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T13:09:15.324698-08:00","close_reason":"Root cause: GetBlockingDependencies treated all deps as blocking when status != closed. Fix: parent-child deps now only block when parent is 'open', not 'in_progress'. Tests: go test ./pkg/beads/... -run TestGetBlockingDependencies - 11 passed (6 original + 5 new parent-child tests). Commit: 5538c022","labels":["triage:ready"]}
