{"id":"orch-go-1m8q","title":"Usage stats in navbar unclear - '40% 5h 25% wk' not immediately understandable","description":"## Problem\n\nThe usage stats shown as '40% 5h 25% wk personal' are cryptic. Users need to decipher what each number means.\n\n## Evidence\n\nScreenshot shows: '40% 5h 25% wk personal • connected'\n\nMeaning (if you know):\n- 40% = hourly usage\n- 5h = hours until reset\n- 25% = weekly usage  \n- wk = weekly indicator\n- personal = account name\n\n## Expected\n\nMake usage immediately understandable:\n- Add labels: '40% hourly | 25% weekly'\n- Or use icons with tooltips\n- Or restructure: '25% weekly (40% this hour) • resets in 5h'\n- Show which limit is constraining (hourly vs weekly)\n\n## Files\n- web/src/routes/+page.svelte - navbar usage display\n- cmd/orch/serve.go - usage API response","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-24T14:23:55.72507-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-24T14:32:32.284904-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-24T14:32:32.284904-08:00","close_reason":"Added tooltips and clearer labels to navbar usage stats. Changes: 5h→5hr, wk→week, added | separator, tooltips explain rolling window and weekly reset. Commit 28fe665."}
