{"id":"orch-go-1wi","title":"POC: Port Python's standalone + API discovery approach to orch-go.","description":"POC: Port Python's standalone + API discovery approach to orch-go. Implement in pkg/tmux/tmux.go: 1) WaitForOpenCodeReady() - poll tmux pane for TUI indicators (┃ prompt box + agent/build text), 2) Modify BuildSpawnCommand to use standalone mode (opencode {dir} --model {model}) instead of attach mode, 3) Add SendPromptAfterReady() - wait for TUI, sleep 1s, send-keys -l prompt, Enter. Reference: orch-cli/src/orch/spawn.py:959-1032 and spawn.py:1083-1127. Test by running orch-go spawn and verifying TUI renders correctly in tmux window.","notes":"workspace: .orch/workspace/og-feat-poc-port-python-20dec","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T09:54:19.36334-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-20T10:09:42.631294-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-20T10:09:42.631294-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-1xrx","title":"Epic: Dashboard 'Needs Attention' Redesign","description":"## Problem\n\nThe dashboard 'Needs Attention' section is broken in multiple ways:\n- Shows noise, not actionable items\n- 'Pending Reviews' with 72 items creates anxiety, not action\n- 'Blocked issues' surfaces expected behavior (sequential deps) as problems\n- No clear actions - items shown without verbs/commands\n\n## Goal\n\nTransform 'Needs Attention' from overwhelming backlog into focused decision surface.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] Small actionable count (3-5 items max normally)\n- [ ] Each item has a clear action verb\n- [ ] Only surfaces items requiring human intervention\n- [ ] Dismissed items don't resurface inappropriately\n\n## Child Issues\n\nConsolidates:\n- orch-go-fqb8: Redesign for actionable decisions (broad scope)\n- orch-go-t404: Blocked issues misleading (specific fix)\n- orch-go-va5v: Replace 'Pending Reviews' with 'Recent Knowledge'\n\n## Design Direction\n\nFrom orch-go-fqb8:\n```\nNeeds Attention (3)\n\n🔴 BLOCKING: 2 agents at Phase: Complete need review\n   → Click to complete\n\n⚠️  DECISION NEEDED: 1 issue needs triage\n   → Click to triage\n\n📊 PATTERN: 'chrome launch' gap recurring (5x)\n   → Consider: kn constrain\n```\n\nCategories prioritized: BLOCKING \u003e DECISION NEEDED \u003e PATTERNS","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2025-12-29T07:37:46.048644-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T14:24:26.865325-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T14:24:26.865325-08:00","close_reason":"Already completed: 🔴 BLOCKING: 2 agents at Phase: Complete need review","labels":["blocked"]}
{"id":"orch-go-1ys","title":"[orch-go] investigation: race test delta unique","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T08:23:53.0987-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-20T09:14:39.761891-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-20T09:14:39.761891-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-20901","title":"Startup hooks inject stale session handoffs after session end","description":"## Problem\nSession handoffs continue to be injected via startup hooks even after `orch session end` completes. The injected handoff is stale/outdated.\n\n## Observed Behavior\n- Ran `orch session end` successfully\n- Started new session\n- Startup hook injected handoff from the *old* session (decidability graph work) instead of fresh state\n\n## Likely Root Cause\nIncomplete session ending - something in the session end flow isn't clearing/updating state that the handoff injection relies on.\n\n## Components to Investigate\n- `orch session end` - what does it archive/clear?\n- `~/.config/opencode/plugin/session-resume.js` - handoff injection logic\n- `orch session resume --check` and `--for-injection` - what determines \"current\" handoff\n- `.orch/session/{name}/latest` symlink - is it being updated correctly?\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- After `orch session end`, new sessions should NOT inject the old handoff\n- Either: handoff cleared, or staleness detected and injection skipped","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-19T15:36:08.895739-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-19T15:47:21.73317-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-19T15:47:21.73317-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Fixed stale handoff injection by gating cross-window scan and legacy fallback on active/ directory presence. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/... -run TestDiscoverSessionHandoff - 11 passed, 0 failed. Investigation at .kb/investigations/2026-01-19-inv-stale-session-handoffs-injected-after.md"}
{"id":"orch-go-20902","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Investigate why Dylan's disk fills up daily. Th...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-25T17:55:21.934185-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-25T18:41:07.284505-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-25T18:41:07.284505-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20902","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating disk consumption patterns, checking large files modified today","created_at":"2026-01-25T17:55:36.406098-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20902","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-25-inv-investigate-dylan-disk-fills-up.md","created_at":"2026-01-25T17:55:56.875687-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20902","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Investigating - Found colima VM consuming 47GB with I/O errors; checking other consumers","created_at":"2026-01-25T18:11:21.817893-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-20902","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Documenting - ROOT CAUSE: Chrome code_sign_clone at 46GB (92GB logical), colima 24GB with I/O errors. 39 Chrome clones never cleaned.","created_at":"2026-01-25T18:19:57.85558-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-20902","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Found root cause: Chrome code_sign_clone (46GB, 39 clones) and corrupted colima (24GB). Investigation with recommendations committed.","created_at":"2026-01-25T18:22:07.627112-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20903","title":"Should we adopt native Claude orchestration over orch-ecosystem?","description":"## Context\n\nAnthropic's native multi-agent orchestration (tengu_brass_pebble / sneakpeek unlock) provides:\n- TeammateTool with spawning, messaging, plan approval, shutdown coordination\n- Task primitives with dependency tracking (blocks/blockedBy)\n- Native skill loading via Skill tool\n\n## The Question\n\nWhat parts of the orch-ecosystem are worth maintaining given native capabilities?\n\n## Blocking Questions\n\nThis gate is blocked by factual questions that require empirical testing:\n1. Is native spawning sufficient?\n2. Is native skill loading sufficient?\n3. Does kb context injection improve outcomes?\n4. Does beads add value over native Task?\n5. Does explicit authority delegation improve outcomes?\n\n## Resolution\n\nOnce blocking questions are answered, Dylan decides what to:\n- Deprecate (native is sufficient)\n- Maintain (unique value)\n- Integrate (hybrid approach)\n\n## References\n\n- `.kb/investigations/2026-01-24-inv-claude-sneakpeek-comparison.md`\n- `.kb/models/decidability-graph.md`","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"question","created_at":"2026-01-25T17:55:55.938188-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T10:32:57.776487-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T10:32:57.776487-08:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"orch-go-20903","depends_on_id":"orch-go-20904","type":"blocks","created_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},{"issue_id":"orch-go-20903","depends_on_id":"orch-go-20905","type":"blocks","created_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},{"issue_id":"orch-go-20903","depends_on_id":"orch-go-20906","type":"blocks","created_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},{"issue_id":"orch-go-20903","depends_on_id":"orch-go-20907","type":"blocks","created_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},{"issue_id":"orch-go-20903","depends_on_id":"orch-go-20908","type":"blocks","created_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"}],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20903","author":"dylanconlin","text":"## Session Summary: 2026-01-25\n\n### Accomplished\n- Read 3 sneakpeek investigations (comparison, setup, native API surface)\n- Designed test protocol with 5 blocking questions (Q1-Q5)\n- Created decidability graph structure in beads\n- Reviewed Test 1 results (native swarm mode via sneakpeek)\n- **Closed Q1**: Native sufficient for coordination, insufficient for project context\n- Added evidence to Q3: Investigation file saved to wrong location (~/.kb/ vs project .kb/)\n- Spawned `orch-go-20910`: Investigation into swarm internals (messaging, pinned messages, other gates, fingerprinting)\n\n### Key Findings from Test 1\n- Native TeammateTool spawning works well\n- Inter-agent messaging is impressive (seamless coordination)\n- **Critical gap**: Agents lack project context awareness\n- Tasks are per-agent, not team-shared (coordination via messages)\n- Shutdown and cleanup workflows work\n\n### Blocking Questions Status\n| ID | Question | Status |\n|----|----------|--------|\n| orch-go-20904 | Native spawning sufficient? | **CLOSED** |\n| orch-go-20905 | Native skill loading sufficient? | Open |\n| orch-go-20906 | kb context improves outcomes? | Open (has evidence) |\n| orch-go-20907 | Beads adds value over native Task? | Open |\n| orch-go-20908 | Authority delegation improves outcomes? | Open |\n\n### Pending\n- `orch-go-20910` investigation will inform Q2 and integration possibilities\n- Q3 can likely close based on Test 1 evidence (wrong file location)\n- Q4/Q5 need targeted tests or can close based on reasoning\n\n### Artifacts\n- Test 1 transcript: `pkg/daemon/orch-go-20904-session-transcript.txt`\n- Investigation (wrong location): `~/.kb/investigations/2026-01-25-inv-daemon-double-spawn-race-conditions.md`\n\n### Resume Point\nCheck `orch-go-20910` results, then close remaining questions or run additional tests.","created_at":"2026-01-25T19:36:08.600493-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20904","title":"Is native spawning sufficient? (Test 1)","description":"## Test Protocol\n\n**Approach:** Exploratory - run real task through native swarm mode, document experience.\n\n**Task:** Something with natural decomposition (investigation → implementation)\n\n**What to observe:**\n- Setup friction (getting swarm mode working)\n- Coordination patterns (team leader behavior)\n- Visibility (can you see what agents are doing?)\n- Handoff quality (investigator → implementer)\n- Approval workflow feel\n- Completion detection\n- Artifact production and location\n- Recovery from failure\n\n**Compare against:** orch spawn --backend claude --tmux\n\n**Success criteria for native:**\n- Spawns successfully without excessive manual intervention\n- Produces equivalent quality output\n- Provides adequate visibility\n- Can be monitored/interrupted","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"question","created_at":"2026-01-25T17:56:04.321621-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-25T18:37:58.773855-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-25T18:37:58.773855-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20904","author":"dylanconlin","text":"## Test 1 Results: Native Swarm Mode Evaluation\n\n### What Worked Well\n- Team creation and agent spawning via Task tool with team_name\n- Inter-agent messaging (`send message to:`, `broadcast`) - seamless coordination\n- Task dependencies (`blockedBy`) respected automatically\n- Autonomous work - agents completed complex tasks independently\n- Clean investigation → implementation handoff\n- Shutdown coordination and resource cleanup\n\n### Critical Gap: Project Context Awareness\n\n**Evidence:** Investigation file saved to wrong location:\n- Expected: `/Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/`\n- Actual: `/Users/dylanconlin/.kb/investigations/`\n\nNative agent had no awareness of:\n- Which project it was working in\n- Where project artifacts belong\n- The project's kb structure\n\n### Additional Gaps\n- Tasks per-agent, not team-shared (coordination requires explicit messaging)\n- Loaded skills polluted native behavior (tried `orch spawn` first)\n- No beads tracking (work completed but no Phase visibility)\n\n### What Native Does Better\n- Inter-agent messaging (direct coordination, not through orchestrator)\n- Simpler setup (no SPAWN_CONTEXT generation)\n- Built-in tmux panes\n- Native task dependencies\n\n### What Orch Does Better\n- Project context (agents know where artifacts belong)\n- kb injection (decisions, constraints, failed attempts)\n- Beads tracking (phase visibility, issue lifecycle)\n- Cross-project awareness\n\n## Conclusion\n\n**Native spawning is sufficient for coordination but insufficient for project-aware work.**\n\nNative could replace `orch spawn` for simple multi-agent tasks. For project work requiring artifacts in correct locations, kb context injection remains necessary.\n\n## Artifacts\n- Transcript: `pkg/daemon/orch-go-20904-session-transcript.txt`\n- Investigation (wrong location): `~/.kb/investigations/2026-01-25-inv-daemon-double-spawn-race-conditions.md`\n- Implementation commit: `ddc41a95` (382 lines, telemetry for dedup layers)","created_at":"2026-01-25T18:37:47.924597-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20905","title":"Is native skill loading sufficient? (Test 2)","description":"## Test Protocol\n\n**Compare:** Native on-demand skill invocation vs SPAWN_CONTEXT full injection\n\n**Task:** Investigation task (same skill content both ways)\n\n**Measurements:**\n- Skill adherence (followed structure?)\n- Artifact production (investigation file created?)\n- Phase discipline (tracked phases?)\n- Evidence quality (sources cited?)\n\n**Success criteria for native:**\n- Investigation file created with proper structure\n- D.E.K.N. summary present\n- Evidence explicitly cited\n- \"What's tested\" vs \"What's untested\" distinction made","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"question","created_at":"2026-01-25T17:56:11.323921-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T12:24:22.582882-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T12:24:22.582882-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-20906","title":"Does kb context injection improve outcomes? (Test 3)","description":"## Test Protocol\n\n**Compare:** Task without kb context vs same task with kb context injected\n\n**Task:** Something that touches area with existing decisions/constraints\n\n**Measurements:**\n- Constraint violations (did it violate known constraints?)\n- Repeated failures (did it try approaches we know don't work?)\n- Decision conflicts (did it contradict prior decisions?)\n- Discovery time (how long to understand existing patterns?)\n\n**Success criteria for kb context:**\n- Avoids at least one failure that no-context version hit\n- References prior decisions appropriately\n- Doesn't violate documented constraints\n\n**Unique value hypothesis:** This is where orch-ecosystem may have irreplaceable value - native has no equivalent to kb context injection.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"question","created_at":"2026-01-25T17:56:19.711245-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T12:24:22.582908-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T12:24:22.582908-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20906","author":"dylanconlin","text":"## Evidence from Test 1 (Native Swarm Mode)\n\n**Direct evidence that kb context injection improves outcomes:**\n\nThe investigator agent saved its investigation file to the wrong location:\n- Expected: `/Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/`  \n- Actual: `/Users/dylanconlin/.kb/investigations/`\n\nWithout kb context injection, the agent:\n- Didn't know which project it was working in\n- Didn't know project artifact conventions\n- Defaulted to global ~/.kb/ location\n\nWith SPAWN_CONTEXT (which includes project path and kb structure), this error would not occur.\n\n**Conclusion:** kb context injection prevents artifact location errors and ensures project-aware behavior.\n\n**Status:** Can close this question based on Test 1 evidence, or run additional targeted test for constraint/decision awareness.","created_at":"2026-01-25T18:38:09.483694-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20907","title":"Does beads add value over native Task? (Test 4)","description":"## Test Protocol\n\n**Compare:** Multi-session work with native Task storage vs beads\n\n**Task:** Multi-day feature implementation requiring context recovery\n\n**Measurements:**\n- Context recovery time (time to productive work after resume)\n- Lost decisions (decisions made but forgotten)\n- Cross-project awareness (can reference work in other repos?)\n- History accessibility (can query what was tried before?)\n\n**Success criteria for beads:**\n- Faster context recovery (\u003c 5 min vs \u003e 10 min)\n- No lost decisions on resume\n- Cross-project references work\n\n**Unique value hypothesis:** Git sync, SQLite durability, cross-project awareness, decidability graph semantics - native Task is simpler but lacks these.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"question","created_at":"2026-01-25T17:56:31.483177-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T12:24:22.582912-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T12:24:22.582912-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-20908","title":"Does explicit authority delegation improve outcomes? (Test 5)","description":"## Test Protocol\n\n**Compare:** Task without authority guidance vs same task with \"decide X, escalate Y\" guidance\n\n**Task:** Task with inherent ambiguity requiring judgment\n\n**Measurements:**\n- Escalation quality (escalated appropriately?)\n- Autonomy quality (decided appropriately?)\n- Scope creep (made changes outside scope?)\n- Blocking rate (stopped for unnecessary questions?)\n\n**Success criteria for authority guidance:**\n- Fewer unnecessary escalations\n- No out-of-scope changes\n- Appropriate escalation on genuinely ambiguous items\n\n**Hypothesis:** Explicit authority delegation is part of \"orchestrator scopes context\" - may be essential for efficient human-AI collaboration.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"question","created_at":"2026-01-25T17:56:31.547219-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T12:24:22.582915-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T12:24:22.582915-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-20909","title":"Reduce daemon log verbosity - logs 270k lines/day","description":"The orch daemon logs every 'Skipping X (missing label triage:ready)' message for every issue in every project, every poll cycle (1 min). With hundreds of issues, this generates ~17MB/day of logs.\n\n**Evidence:**\n- daemon.log hit 867k lines (54MB) in 3 days\n- Caused Claude Code crash from disk full on 2026-01-24\n- Jan 21 investigation missed this (focused on skill-reprocess)\n\n**Fix options:**\n1. Only log spawnable issues, not skipped ones\n2. Log skip summary per project ('Skipped 45 issues in orch-cli') instead of each\n3. Add --verbose flag, default to quiet\n\n**Location:** orch-go daemon code (poll loop logging)","repro":"tail -f ~/.orch/daemon.log shows hundreds of 'Skipping X' lines per minute","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-25T18:00:29.965088-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-25T19:34:29.427605-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-25T19:34:29.427605-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20909","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating daemon log verbosity issue in pkg/daemon/","created_at":"2026-01-25T18:42:52.635128-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20909","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Fix: Log skip summary per project instead of each individual issue. Will reduce ~1000 lines/cycle to ~10 lines/cycle.","created_at":"2026-01-25T18:44:07.395868-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20909","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Fix verified. Reduced daemon verbose log volume from ~270k lines/day to ~2k lines/day by replacing per-issue skip logs with per-project summaries. Tests: go test ./pkg/daemon/... - PASS (2.396s)","created_at":"2026-01-25T18:47:18.986243-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20910","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Investigate how Claude Code's native swarm mode...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-25T18:50:13.956493-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-25T19:38:11.953269-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-25T19:38:11.953269-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20910","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating Claude Code native swarm internals and sneakpeek reverse engineering","created_at":"2026-01-25T18:50:27.54393-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20910","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-25-inv-investigate-claude-code-native-swarm.md","created_at":"2026-01-25T18:50:35.664504-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20910","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Investigated Claude Code native swarm internals. Key findings: JSON file-based mailboxes for inter-agent messaging, single tengu_brass_pebble gate controls all multi-agent features, fingerprint isolation via CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR (simpler than Docker). Recommended hybrid approach: native swarm for quick tasks, orch-go for tracked orchestration. See investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-25-inv-investigate-claude-code-native-swarm.md","created_at":"2026-01-25T18:58:56.598109-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20911","title":"[orch-go] research: Research macOS Sequoia Chrome code_sign_clone d...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-25T19:41:32.988386-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-25T20:49:11.523605-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-25T20:49:11.523605-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20911","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Researching macOS Sequoia Chrome code_sign_clone disk space issue","created_at":"2026-01-25T19:41:43.849947-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20911","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-25-inv-research-macos-sequoia-chrome-code-sign-clone.md","created_at":"2026-01-25T19:41:52.872894-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20911","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Research complete. Chrome's MacAppCodeSignClone feature creates ~1.2GB clones on each launch; cleanup only works on clean exit. Workarounds: (1) launchd cleanup script, (2) --disable-features=MacAppCodeSignClone flag, (3) reboot more frequently. All Chromium browsers affected. See investigation file for details.","created_at":"2026-01-25T19:48:31.624521-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20912","title":"orch frontier: Show blocker in BLOCKED section","description":"The BLOCKED section shows blocked issues but doesn't show what's blocking them. The help text mentions 'sorted by leverage (what would unblock the most)' but the output doesn't surface dependency info.\n\n**Current:**\n```\nBLOCKED (4)\n   orch-go-kz7zr  Epic: Governance Infrastructure...\n```\n\n**Proposed:**\n```\nBLOCKED (4)\n   orch-go-kz7zr  Epic: Governance Infrastructure...  ← blocked by orch-go-20903\n```\n\nThis helps orchestrators immediately see what to unblock without running `bd show` on each item.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:16:06.944054-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T21:21:35.158869-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T21:21:35.158869-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20912","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating blocked section output format","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:17:17.537171-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20912","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Adding blocker info to frontier BLOCKED section","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:17:57.340314-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20912","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added blocker info to BLOCKED section in orch frontier. Now shows '← blocked by: [ids]' under each blocked issue. Tests: go test ./pkg/frontier/... ./cmd/orch/... - all passed.","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:21:04.786919-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20913","title":"orch frontier: Show issue type in READY section","description":"The ACTIVE section shows skill type `(investigation)` but the READY section doesn't show issue type. Adding type would help with triage.\n\n**Current:**\n```\nREADY TO RELEASE (61)\n   orch-go-sryez  Orchestration gap: practical validation skipped...\n   orch-go-g3daa  [orch-go] architect: Design worker detection fo...\n```\n\n**Proposed:**\n```\nREADY TO RELEASE (61)\n   orch-go-sryez  [bug] Orchestration gap: practical validation skipped...\n   orch-go-g3daa  [task] architect: Design worker detection fo...\n```\n\nNote: JSON output already includes `issue_type` - this is just surfacing it in human-readable output.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:16:08.574318-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T21:21:36.11352-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T21:21:36.11352-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20913","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Analyzing READY section output and bd ready command","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:17:22.491824-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20913","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Adding issue type to READY section text output","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:17:57.099181-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20913","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Tests: make build - successful. Added [type] prefix to READY section in orch frontier output (e.g., [bug], [task], [feature], [question]). Issue types now visible at a glance.","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:19:20.061887-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20914","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Why do we have 212 stuck agents? Analyze the st...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:17:15.329371-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T21:21:36.35245-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T21:21:36.35245-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20914","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Analyzing 212 stuck agents: registry vs OpenCode sessions comparison","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:17:27.250352-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20914","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-25-inv-212-stuck-agents-analysis.md","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:19:45.504134-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20914","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Investigation complete. 212 stuck agents are orphaned registry entries from completed agents. Registry status is never updated (by design). Recommendation: Update frontier API to use tmux+OpenCode sources like status command does. See investigation file for full analysis.","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:24:55.131018-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20915","title":"[orch-go] feature-impl: Fix frontier API stuck calculation to use tmux+...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:36:42.002821-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T11:03:12.293908-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T11:03:12.293908-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20915","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Reading investigation and relevant source files","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:36:55.922044-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20915","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Replace getActiveAndStuckAgents() to use tmux+OpenCode instead of registry 2. Keep 2h stuck threshold 3. Remove registry import","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:37:21.330075-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20915","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Rewriting getActiveAndStuckAgents() to use tmux+OpenCode pattern from status_cmd.go","created_at":"2026-01-25T21:37:28.626225-08:00"}]}
