{"id":"orch-go-20981","title":"[orch-go] feature-impl: Disable the orchestrator coaching plugin. The p...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-28T10:36:30.754789-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-28T10:36:55.153182-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-28T10:36:55.153182-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20981","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Disabling orchestrator coaching plugin that causes confusion for worker agents","created_at":"2026-01-28T10:36:45.963341-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20982","title":"[orch-go] feature-impl: Fix orchestrator coaching plugin worker detecti...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-28T10:40:25.161958-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-28T12:03:28.732558-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-28T12:03:28.732558-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20982","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Fixing coaching plugin worker detection by adding ORCH_WORKER=1 env var","created_at":"2026-01-28T10:40:44.667836-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20982","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Modify orch spawn to set ORCH_WORKER=1 env var for workers 2. Update coaching.ts to check process.env.ORCH_WORKER instead of directory detection 3. Create symlink to re-enable plugin 4. Restart opencode","created_at":"2026-01-28T10:40:50.077313-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20983","title":"[orch-go] architect: The orchestrator coaching plugin cannot reliabl...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-28T10:42:40.421706-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-28T11:49:07.567823-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-28T11:49:07.567823-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20983","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Synthesizing - Confirmed title-based detection works (this session has zero coaching metrics), now documenting the architectural fork and recommendation","created_at":"2026-01-28T10:43:46.25279-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20983","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Investigation confirms title-based worker detection IS working (verified: this session has zero coaching metrics despite 30+ tool calls). Root cause is architectural: plugins run in server process, can't see agent env vars. Recommendation: accept current detection as 'good enough', document limitations, create upstream OpenCode issue for proper metadata exposure. Investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-28-inv-orchestrator-coaching-plugin-cannot-reliably.md","created_at":"2026-01-28T10:46:10.770589-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20984","title":"Update coaching plugin to use session.metadata.role for worker detection","description":"Once OpenCode exposes session.metadata.role from the x-opencode-env-ORCH_WORKER header, simplify coaching.ts to use metadata.role directly instead of title-based heuristics. This depends on the OpenCode fork change being completed first. Reference: .kb/investigations/2026-01-28-inv-orchestrator-coaching-plugin-cannot-reliably.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-28T10:48:34.714553-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-28T11:44:00.765761-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-28T11:44:00.765761-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20984","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Simplifying coaching plugin to use session.metadata.role instead of title-based heuristics","created_at":"2026-01-28T10:55:59.279545-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20984","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Simplify session.created event to use only metadata.role. 2. Remove complex detection functions (detectWorkerViaAPI, isWorkerByTitle, detectWorkerSession). 3. Simplify tool.execute.after worker check to cache-only lookup. 4. Update comments to reflect new architecture.","created_at":"2026-01-28T10:56:36.537033-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20984","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Simplified coaching plugin to use session.metadata.role for worker detection. Removed complex helper functions (detectWorkerViaAPI, isWorkerByTitle, detectWorkerSession). Updated session.created event handler and tool hooks to use cache-only lookups.","created_at":"2026-01-28T10:59:14.581723-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-20984","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Investigation complete. Root cause: OpenCode fix for session.metadata.role EXISTS (commit bbf798911) but server needs restart. Solution: overmind restart opencode to pick up the fix. See .kb/investigations/2026-01-28-inv-coaching-plugin-still-fires-workers.md","created_at":"2026-01-28T11:20:32.072445-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20985","title":"Auto-rebuild OpenCode binary when fork changes are detected","description":"When spawning workers that depend on OpenCode fork features (like session.metadata.role), the binary should be automatically rebuilt if the fork has uncommitted or recent changes. Currently workers use stale binaries and features don't work until manual rebuild. Similar to how orch auto-rebuilds orch-go binary.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-28T11:06:23.581928-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T20:00:43.684868-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20985","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Auto-rebuild OpenCode binary when fork changes detected","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:47:32.404341-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20985","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Detect OpenCode fork changes at ~/Documents/personal/Claude 2. Auto-rebuild OpenCode binary (bun run build) when stale 3. Integrate with worker spawn process 4. Similar pattern to existing orch-go auto-rebuild","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:48:02.372884-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20986","title":"Audit rebuild-on-change mechanisms across orch ecosystem","description":"Audit all ~10 repos in the orch ecosystem (orch-go, kb-cli, beads, beads-ui-svelte, glass, skillc, agentlog, kn, orch-cli, orch-knowledge) for:\n\n1. What artifacts need rebuilding on code changes? (binaries, compiled skills, generated files)\n2. How is staleness detected? (version --source, git hash comparison, none?)\n3. How is rebuild triggered? (post-commit hook, make install, launchd, manual?)\n4. What's the failure mode if rebuild is missed?\n\nProduce investigation with:\n- Matrix of repos × rebuild mechanisms\n- Gaps identified (repos with no staleness detection, no auto-rebuild)\n- Recommendations for consistency and automation\n\nReference: ~/.orch/ECOSYSTEM.md for repo list and existing CLI Binaries section","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-28T11:11:22.415498-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-28T11:41:46.381007-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-28T11:41:46.381007-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20986","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Auditing rebuild-on-change mechanisms across all orch ecosystem repos","created_at":"2026-01-28T11:11:51.396344-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20986","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-28-inv-audit-rebuild-change-mechanisms-across.md","created_at":"2026-01-28T11:12:04.615104-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20986","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Audit found 3 rebuild mechanisms (post-commit hooks 40%, orch complete, manual), critical gaps in glass/agentlog (no version commands), detailed matrix and recommendations in investigation file","created_at":"2026-01-28T11:25:42.993442-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20987","title":"[orch-go] architect: Design systemic solution for ecosystem rebuild-...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-28T11:27:33.156395-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-28T11:39:17.796582-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-28T11:39:17.796582-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20987","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Reviewing rebuild-on-change investigation, identifying decision forks for unified solution","created_at":"2026-01-28T11:27:44.339049-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20987","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-28-inv-design-systemic-solution-ecosystem-rebuild.md","created_at":"2026-01-28T11:27:59.287952-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20987","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Exploration - 5 forks identified. Key finding: glass/agentlog already have on-demand auto-rebuild mechanism but lack version command for external staleness detection","created_at":"2026-01-28T11:28:37.70264-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-20987","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Designed three-layer ecosystem rebuild architecture: (1) On-demand auto-rebuild (already exists in glass/agentlog), (2) Version commands (missing in glass/agentlog - feat-054/055), (3) Expanded orch doctor (feat-056). Key finding: 'gaps' are smaller than audit suggested - glass/agentlog have BEST rebuild mechanism, just missing observability layer.","created_at":"2026-01-28T11:31:59.211579-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20988","title":"orch cannot inspect OpenCode sessions not spawned via orch spawn","description":"**Problem:**\nWhen an OpenCode session exists but wasn't spawned via `orch spawn`, orchestrators have no way to inspect it.\n\n**Impact:**\n- Orchestrators fumble trying to find agent output\n- Sessions started outside orch workflow become invisible\n- Manual correlation required between OpenCode dashboard and orch tooling\n\n**Potential solutions:**\n1. `orch tail` should fall back to querying OpenCode API directly by session ID\n2. `orch status` should show ALL OpenCode sessions, marking orch-tracked vs untracked\n3. Surface session-to-workspace mapping in orch tooling","repro":"1. Note an OpenCode session ID from dashboard (format: opencode-untracked-NNNN)\n2. Run: orch tail opencode-untracked-NNNN\n3. Observe: 'no agent found for beads ID' error\n4. Run: orch status --all\n5. Observe: session not listed","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-28T11:32:12.990194-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T19:43:05.57782-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T19:43:05.57782-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20988","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Analyzing how orch interacts with OpenCode API to identify gaps in inspecting non-orch-spawned sessions","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:36:48.359647-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20988","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating how orch can inspect OpenCode sessions not spawned via orch spawn","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:36:49.070069-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20988","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-orch-cannot-inspect-opencode-sessions.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:36:55.949737-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-20988","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-orch-cannot-inspect-opencode-sessions.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:37:05.122604-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-20988","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Exploration - Analyzed OpenCode session discovery. Found that sessions without [beads-id] pattern in title are invisible to orch tooling. 10 untracked sessions found in current instance.","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:37:31.260072-08:00"},{"id":6,"issue_id":"orch-go-20988","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Reproduction verified: Tested orch status --all - now shows 'Untracked: 1' in header and displays untracked session with STATUS=untracked. Tested orch tail --session ses_xxx - successfully displays output from untracked session (title: 'System reliability and hardening discussion'). Bug is fixed.","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:40:21.221459-08:00"},{"id":7,"issue_id":"orch-go-20988","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Reproduction verified: orch tail --session ses_xxx now successfully fetches messages from any OpenCode session (tested with ses_3f30689ebffeBb6HL1yuXUw0l9). orch status --all shows untracked sessions with session IDs. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/... - 30+ tests passing","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:42:26.790351-08:00"},{"id":8,"issue_id":"orch-go-20988","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added orch tail --session flag for direct session ID access to non-orch-spawned sessions. Enhanced orch status to display untracked sessions with truncated session IDs. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/... - 30+ tests passing, 0 failed.","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:42:30.471821-08:00"},{"id":9,"issue_id":"orch-go-20988","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Implemented untracked session visibility in orch status (--all shows Untracked: N count and session rows with STATUS=untracked). orch tail --session ses_xxx enables direct inspection. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/... -run 'Status|Swarm|Tail' - 30+ tests pass. Bug reproduction verified fixed.","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:42:37.537638-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20989","title":"Add version command to glass CLI","description":"Add 'glass version' subcommand exposing build-time version info (Version, BuildTime, SourceDir, GitHash). Support --json flag for machine-readable output. Variables already defined in main.go via ldflags. Enables staleness detection by orch doctor.\n\nPattern: Follow orch, kb, skillc version commands.\nAcceptance: 'glass version' outputs human-readable, 'glass version --json' outputs JSON.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-28T11:38:32.086552-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T11:02:38.245902-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T11:02:38.245902-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-20990","title":"Add version command to agentlog CLI","description":"Add 'agentlog version' subcommand exposing build-time version info. Uses cobra pattern. Support --json flag. Enables staleness detection by orch doctor.\n\nAcceptance: 'agentlog version' and 'agentlog version --json' work.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-28T11:38:37.173849-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T11:02:37.354773-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T11:02:37.354773-08:00"}
