{"id":"orch-go-20997","title":"Add version command to glass CLI","description":"Add 'glass version' and 'glass version --json' subcommand. Glass already has ldflags (Version, BuildTime, SourceDir, GitHash) - just needs ~30 lines to expose them. Follow orch version pattern. Enables orch doctor to verify glass binary staleness.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-28T13:16:44.157636-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T11:02:51.562045-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T11:02:51.562045-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20997","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Add 'glass version' subcommand 2. Add 'glass version --json' flag support 3. Expose existing ldflags (Version, BuildTime, SourceDir, GitHash) 4. Follow orch version pattern","created_at":"2026-01-28T13:20:03.763959-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20997","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Adding version command to glass CLI following orch version pattern","created_at":"2026-01-28T13:20:05.877817-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20997","author":"dylanconlin","text":"QUESTION: Cannot locate glass CLI source code in orch-go repo. The task says 'glass already has ldflags' but I cannot find cmd/glass/, tools/glass/, or glass.go anywhere. Is glass in a separate repository? If so, what's the repo path?","created_at":"2026-01-28T13:21:15.137952-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-20997","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Glass repo located at /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/glass, proceeding with version command implementation","created_at":"2026-01-28T13:23:56.170838-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-20997","author":"dylanconlin","text":"CONSTRAINT: Task requires modifying /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/glass/ (separate repo) but my workspace is /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go. This is cross-project work. Reverting unauthorized edits to glass/main.go. Need orchestrator guidance on spawn strategy (spawn in glass repo? --no-track?).","created_at":"2026-01-28T13:24:52.574671-08:00"},{"id":6,"issue_id":"orch-go-20997","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Working in glass repo at ~/Documents/personal/glass/, implementing version command with --json support","created_at":"2026-01-28T13:33:35.163777-08:00"},{"id":7,"issue_id":"orch-go-20997","author":"dylanconlin","text":"IMPORTANT: Glass source is at ~/Documents/personal/glass/ (separate repo, not in orch-go)","created_at":"2026-01-28T13:35:45.366985-08:00"},{"id":8,"issue_id":"orch-go-20997","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Adding version command to glass CLI following orch version pattern","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:47:23.365127-08:00"},{"id":9,"issue_id":"orch-go-20997","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Add 'glass version' command 2. Add 'glass version --json' support 3. Expose ldflags (Version, BuildTime, SourceDir, GitHash) 4. Follow orch version pattern","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:47:29.278123-08:00"}]}
