{"id":"orch-go-21001","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Debug why coaching plugin still fires on worker...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-28T13:37:28.171712-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T10:32:22.011122-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T10:32:22.011122-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21001","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Debugging why coaching plugin fires on workers despite role='worker' metadata","created_at":"2026-01-28T13:37:48.139904-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21001","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Investigating - Root cause found: session.created event does NOT include metadata field. Metadata.role is not accessible in event handler.","created_at":"2026-01-28T13:40:53.220871-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21001","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Root cause identified: metadata.role not in session.created events. Recommendation: revert to title-based detection. Investigation file and SYNTHESIS.md committed.","created_at":"2026-01-28T13:43:08.937126-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21002","title":"Pre-spawn decision check: soft gate for architect decisions","description":"## Problem\n\nArchitect decisions have no teeth. The coaching plugin failure showed:\n- Architect produced recommendations\n- Orchestrator/agents spawned tactical work anyway\n- 18 investigations, contradictory conclusions, no enforcement\n\nDecisions exist but don't constrain future work.\n\n## Solution\n\nAdd pre-spawn decision check to `orch spawn`:\n\n```\norch spawn investigation \"fix coaching plugin worker detection\"\n\n⚠️ DECISION CONFLICT: 2026-01-28-coaching-plugin-disabled.md\n   \"No more local fixes without OpenCode upstream changes\"\n   \nTo proceed: --acknowledge-decision \u003cdecision-id\u003e\n```\n\n## Implementation\n\n1. Before spawning, query kb for decisions related to task\n   - Match on keywords in task description\n   - Match on file patterns if decision declares them\n   \n2. If matching decision found:\n   - Display warning with decision summary\n   - Require `--acknowledge-decision \u003cid\u003e` flag to proceed\n   - Log the override for visibility\n\n3. Decision frontmatter support (optional):\n   ```yaml\n   blocks:\n     - keywords: [\"coaching plugin\", \"worker detection\"]\n     - patterns: [\"**/coaching*\"]\n   ```\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Spawning to an area with an architect decision shows warning\n- Override requires explicit flag (visible, intentional)\n- Overrides are logged for pattern detection\n\n## References\n\n- `.kb/decisions/2026-01-28-coaching-plugin-disabled.md` - Example decision that should have blocked spawns\n- `kb-9c8c38` - Constraint: agent \"fixed\" claims require human verification\n- Discussion: 18 investigations on coaching plugin, no synthesis enforcement","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-28T14:14:32.668476-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-28T14:37:29.457237-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-28T14:37:29.457237-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21002","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Implementing pre-spawn decision check soft gate","created_at":"2026-01-28T14:27:59.391643-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21002","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Query kb for decisions matching task keywords 2. Match file patterns from decision frontmatter 3. Display warning when decision found 4. Require --acknowledge-decision flag to override 5. Log overrides to ~/.orch/decision-overrides.jsonl 6. Support decision frontmatter 'blocks' field","created_at":"2026-01-28T14:28:08.975464-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21002","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Design - Implementation approach: 1) Add --acknowledge-decision flag to spawn cmd 2) Create checkDecisionConflicts() in spawn_validation.go 3) Parse decision frontmatter for 'blocks' field (YAML) 4) Match task keywords against blocked keywords/patterns 5) Display warning + require flag override 6) Log overrides to ~/.orch/decision-overrides.jsonl","created_at":"2026-01-28T14:29:15.213566-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21002","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Implemented pre-spawn decision check soft gate. Added --acknowledge-decision flag, decision frontmatter parsing (blocks.keywords, blocks.patterns), conflict detection with keyword/pattern matching, warning display, and override logging to ~/.orch/decision-overrides.jsonl. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch -run TestCheckDecisionConflicts - 4 test scenarios pass (no conflict, conflict not ack, conflict ack, wrong ID). Manually verified: spawn blocked on keyword match, override allowed with flag, override logged to jsonl. Commit: ed423713","created_at":"2026-01-28T14:36:51.340901-08:00"}]}
