{"id":"orch-go-21005","title":"[orch-go] investigation: debug coaching plugin worker detection","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:00:25.704575-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T10:32:25.360612-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T10:32:25.360612-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-21006","title":"Update decision template with blocks: frontmatter guidance","description":"The decision gate feature (2026-01-28) adds enforcement teeth to decisions via blocks: frontmatter, but the decision template has no mention of this. Workers/orchestrators creating decisions won't know to add blocking keywords.\n\n**Changes needed:**\n1. Update ~/.kb/templates/decision.md - add optional blocks: section after status with guidance comment\n2. Update kb-cli embedded template (cmd/kb/create.go:239) - same change\n3. Update architect skill - when recommending decisions that should constrain future work, suggest blocks: keywords\n4. Update orchestrator skill - add guidance on when to add blocks: during promotion\n\n**Template addition:**\n```yaml\n---\nstatus: active\n# Optional: Gate future spawns that would conflict with this decision\n# blocks:\n#   - keywords:\n#       - [keyword that should trigger this decision]\n#     patterns:\n#       - \"**/path/pattern*\"\n---\n```\n\n**Guidance to add:**\n- Add blocks: when decision resolves recurring issue (3+ prior investigations)\n- Add blocks: when decision establishes constraint future agents might violate\n- Keywords should match how someone would describe the problem in a spawn task\n\nReference: .kb/decisions/2026-01-28-decision-gate.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:20:45.911063-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-28T15:43:12.960103-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-28T15:43:12.960103-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21006","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Locating decision template and understanding frontmatter guidance requirements","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:37:22.997325-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21006","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Update ~/.kb/templates/DECISION.md with blocks: frontmatter guidance 2. Update kb-cli embedded template (cmd/kb/create.go:239) 3. Update architect skill guidance 4. Update orchestrator skill guidance","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:37:38.768796-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21006","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Starting with template updates","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:38:15.268404-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21006","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Validation - Verifying all template changes applied correctly","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:40:45.201517-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21006","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Updated decision templates and skills with blocks: frontmatter guidance\n\nDeliverables:\n1. ~/.kb/templates/DECISION.md - Added blocks: YAML frontmatter example with guidance\n2. kb-cli (cmd/kb/create.go) - Updated embedded decision template with blocks: guidance  \n3. architect skill - Added 'Decision Gate Guidance' section explaining when to suggest blocks:\n4. orchestrator skill - Added 'Decision Promotion with Blocks' section with format and keyword selection guidance\n\nAll changes committed across kb-cli (558e508) and orch-knowledge (c3bd95b, cfa295f).\nSkills rebuilt and deployed to ~/.claude/skills/.\n\nWorkers/orchestrators creating decisions now have template guidance on when and how to add blocks: frontmatter for decision gate enforcement.","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:42:37.060011-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21007","title":"Add decision-patch detection to completion escalation","description":"When a worker completes work that patches or extends an existing decision, the escalation model should detect this and surface an action: Consider adding blocks: keywords to decision X.\n\nContext:\nDecision gate (2026-01-28) blocks spawns when they match decision keywords. But this requires decisions to have blocks: frontmatter. Currently only 2 decisions use this. Rather than relying on orchestrators to remember to add blocks: during promotion, detect at completion time when the completed work relates to an existing decision.\n\nDetection logic:\n1. Parse SYNTHESIS.md for references to .kb/decisions/ files\n2. Check if investigation patches an existing decision (Patches-Decision field in investigation template)\n3. If work patches/extends a decision that lacks blocks: frontmatter - EscalationReview with action suggestion\n\nIntegration with escalation model:\n- Add new check in DetermineEscalation() or as separate post-verification step\n- Surface as action item in completion review\n- Could be Info level (optional) or Review level (mandatory review)\n\nWhy completion time:\n- Context is fresh (just read SYNTHESIS.md, know what decision was relevant)\n- Forcing function (vs relying on memory during promotion)\n- Aligns with Capture at Context principle\n\nReferences:\n- .kb/decisions/2026-01-28-decision-gate.md\n- .kb/decisions/2026-01-17-five-tier-completion-escalation-model.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:21:11.953021-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-28T15:43:13.95687-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-28T15:43:13.95687-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21007","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating completion escalation logic to add decision-patch detection","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:37:33.23884-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21007","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Add function to detect missing blocks: frontmatter in decisions 2. Extend EscalationInput with decision-patch metadata 3. Integrate detection into DetermineEscalationFromCompletion 4. Add escalation logic for missing blocks 5. Write tests 6. Update ExplainEscalation for new case","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:38:19.9613-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21007","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Adding decision-patch detection logic to escalation","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:38:25.39378-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21007","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added decision-patch detection to escalation. Detects when work patches decisions lacking blocks: frontmatter and escalates as EscalationInfo with action suggestion. Tests: go test ./pkg/verify/... - all pass","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:42:29.664179-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21008","title":"skillc: add deployment headers to reference files","description":"Reference files copied during skillc deploy lack the AUTO-GENERATED header that SKILL.md has. This makes the 'don't edit deployed files' contract invisible, leading to edits in ~/.claude/skills/ that get overwritten on next deploy.\n\n**Root cause:** Progressive disclosure design (Jan 2026) introduced reference/ directories for on-demand loading. The design focused on discovery mechanism (direct file paths) but didn't account for edit-time confusion.\n\n**Evidence:** Just hit this - edited ~/.claude/skills/meta/orchestrator/reference/model-selection.md instead of source at ~/orch-knowledge/skills/src/meta/orchestrator/reference/model-selection.md. Edit was overwritten on next deploy.\n\n**Proposed fix:** skillc deploy should add header to copied reference files:\n```\n\u003c!-- Deployed from: ~/orch-knowledge/skills/src/.../reference/... --\u003e\n\u003c!-- To modify: edit source file, then run: skillc deploy --\u003e\n```\n\n**Reference:** .kb/investigations/2026-01-17-inv-design-core-vs-reference-split.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-29T09:56:00.441047-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T10:04:24.177745-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T10:04:19.195403-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21008","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Adding deployment headers to reference files to prevent edits in deployed location","created_at":"2026-01-29T09:56:58.557322-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21008","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Modify handleDeploy to detect reference/ directories 2. Add header generation for reference files 3. Copy reference/ dirs with headers during deployment 4. Test with actual skill deployment","created_at":"2026-01-29T09:59:47.04101-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21008","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Adding reference file copy logic with deployment headers to skillc","created_at":"2026-01-29T09:59:48.372918-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21008","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added deployment headers to reference files. Changes committed to skillc repo (commit 5177ba0). All reference files now show source path and modification instructions when deployed.","created_at":"2026-01-29T10:03:22.194797-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21009","title":"orchestrator skill: move behavioral guides from reference to core","description":"Audit found orchestrator reference files contain behavioral guidance that should always be loaded, not situational lookup content.\n\n**Evidence:**\n- Action log shows only 14 reference file reads in 30 days across all skills\n- Orchestrator has 1463 lines core + 2051 lines reference = 3514 total (fragmented, not reduced)\n- Files like orchestrator-autonomy.md and meta-orchestrator-interface.md are behavioral guides relevant to EVERY action\n\n**Files to move to core:**\n- orchestrator-autonomy.md - Always relevant behavioral guide\n- meta-orchestrator-interface.md - Always relevant interaction patterns\n\n**Files to evaluate (frequently needed):**\n- model-selection.md - Needed at every spawn decision\n- spawning-checklist.md - Needed at every spawn\n\n**Files that correctly belong in reference (situational/lookup):**\n- orch-commands.md - Command lookup\n- dashboard-troubleshooting.md - Error recovery\n- skill-selection-guide.md - On-demand decision trees\n- config-locations.md - Lookup table\n- workspace-architecture.md - Deep detail\n- completion-workflow.md - Situational procedure\n- daemon-operations.md - Ops-specific\n- session-reflection.md - End-of-session only\n\n**Contrast with feature-impl:** Phase-based reference files work correctly - agents load 2-3 of 11 files based on active phases. Orchestrator reference files lack this conditional loading pattern.\n\n**Reference:** Action log analysis showing 14 reads/30 days","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-29T10:02:52.655057-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T20:28:03.7984-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T20:28:03.7984-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21009","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Analyzing orchestrator skill context structure and identifying always-relevant behavioral guides for core context relocation","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:15:32.009329-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21009","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Move orchestrator-autonomy.md from reference to core 2. Move meta-orchestrator-interface.md from reference to core 3. Evaluate model-selection.md and spawning-checklist.md for core relocation 4. Verify reference files remain correctly placed 5. Ensure skillc compilation/deployment works correctly after restructure","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:15:46.964767-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21009","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Analysis complete. orchestrator-autonomy.md (214 lines), meta-orchestrator-interface.md (215 lines), model-selection.md (143 lines), and spawning-checklist.md (209 lines) are all always-relevant and should move to core. Current skill is 16,605 tokens (already over 15,000 budget). Will need to evaluate if budget should be increased or if content can be condensed.","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:17:13.464646-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21009","author":"dylanconlin","text":"QUESTION: Current skill is 16,605 tokens (already over 15,000 budget). Adding ~781 lines of reference content will increase this further. Should I: (A) Move content as-is and increase token budget, (B) Move content but condense it, or (C) Re-evaluate which files to move?","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:17:25.44663-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21009","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Proceeding with Option A (increase token budget). Evidence: reference files only accessed 14x in 30 days, current skill already over budget. Will increase budget to 22,000 tokens to accommodate always-relevant behavioral content.","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:18:59.800946-08:00"},{"id":6,"issue_id":"orch-go-21009","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Completed migration. orchestrator-autonomy.md (214 lines), meta-orchestrator-interface.md (215 lines), model-selection.md (143 lines), and spawning-checklist.md (209 lines) integrated into core template. Token budget increased to 25,000 (currently 23,908). Load-bearing patterns verified. Skill deployed to ~/.claude/skills/. Next: deprecate old reference files.","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:25:15.553476-08:00"},{"id":7,"issue_id":"orch-go-21009","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Successfully relocated 4 always-relevant behavioral guides (orchestrator-autonomy, meta-orchestrator-interface, model-selection, spawning-checklist) from reference files to core orchestrator skill template. Token budget increased from 15K to 25K (currently 23.9K tokens). Reference files deprecated with notices. Skill compiled, validated, and deployed to ~/.claude/skills/. Committed to orch-knowledge.","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:26:56.053335-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21010","title":"daemon: rollback in_progress status when spawn fails","description":"Daemon marks issue as in_progress before spawn, but doesn't rollback when spawn fails.\n\n**Evidence from daemon.log:**\n```\n[orch-go] Spawning work for issue orch-go-21009\n[orch-go] Skipping orch-go-21009: failed to spawn work: exit status 1\n```\n\nIssue orch-go-21009 is now stuck at in_progress with no agent running.\n\n**Expected:** If spawn fails, status should revert to open so the issue can be retried.\n\n**Current behavior:** Status stays in_progress, creating orphaned issues.","repro":"1. Create issue with triage:ready label 2. Daemon picks up issue and marks in_progress 3. Spawn fails (exit status 1) 4. Issue stays in_progress with no agent","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T10:08:24.724122-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T14:07:22.117465-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T14:07:22.117465-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21010","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating daemon spawn flow and beads status management to understand where rollback should occur when spawn fails","created_at":"2026-01-29T14:03:40.051856-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21010","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Implemented status rollback in SpawnWorkForProject when spawn fails. When orch work command fails after status was set to in_progress, the status is now rolled back to open so the issue can be retried. Added TestBug_SpawnFailureDoesNotBlockRetry test and documentation test. Tests: go test ./pkg/daemon/... - all 121 tests passed (2.8s)","created_at":"2026-01-29T14:06:41.984951-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21011","title":"Integrate decision blocking into decidability graph","description":"## Problem\n\nDecision blocking via keyword matching (spawn_validation.go) is redundant with the decidability graph model and causes false positives.\n\n**Current behavior:** Before spawn, task description is matched against decision `blocks:` keywords using substring matching. Common words like 'orchestrator' or 'move' trigger false positives, blocking daemon from spawning legitimate work.\n\n**Root cause:** Decision blocking was implemented before the decidability graph model. It's a spawn-time workaround for what should be graph-level dependencies.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Daemon blocked on 'orchestrator skill: move behavioral guides' because it matched 'orchestrator synthesis' and 'move template to orch' keywords\n- Issue orch-go-21009 is legitimate work that was blocked by false positive keyword matching\n- See daemon.log: multiple 'spawn blocked: decision conflict' errors\n\n## Correct Model (Decidability Graph)\n\nPer .kb/models/decidability-graph.md:\n- Work nodes → daemon traverses freely\n- Question/Gate nodes → block until resolved by appropriate authority\n- Dependencies encoded in beads → bd ready only shows traversable work\n\nAuthority boundaries should be **first-class in the graph**, not bolted on as spawn-time keyword validation.\n\n## Proposed Fix\n\n1. Remove keyword-based decision blocking from spawn path entirely\n2. When a decision has `blocks:` frontmatter, surface it during triage (issue creation/labeling)\n3. If work relates to a blocking decision, create a Question dependency that must be resolved before work proceeds\n4. Daemon only sees work where dependencies are satisfied\n\n## Interim Fix (Already Applied)\n\nSkip decision conflict check for daemon-driven spawns (daemonDriven=true in runSpawnWithSkillInternal). Issues labeled triage:ready have already been validated by orchestrator.\n\n## References\n\n- .kb/models/decidability-graph.md\n- .kb/decisions/2026-01-07-strategic-orchestrator-model.md  \n- cmd/orch/spawn_validation.go (checkDecisionConflicts)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-29T10:21:05.310885-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T10:25:45.721873-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T10:25:45.721873-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-21012","title":"orch spawn shows 'beads lookup failed' warnings for non-existent issues","repro":"Every orch spawn shows warnings like:\nWarning: beads lookup failed for specs-platform-28 (via CLI): failed to parse bd show output: unexpected end of JSON input - treating as closed\nWarning: beads lookup failed for specs-platform-29 (via CLI): ...\nWarning: beads lookup failed for specs-platform-30 (via CLI): ...\n\nThese issues don't exist in beads (bd show returns 'no issue found') but orch is trying to look them up on every spawn.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T10:52:46.422156-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T19:42:03.321114-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T19:42:03.321114-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21012","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating 'beads lookup failed' warnings in orch spawn","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:34:40.999321-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21012","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-orch-spawn-shows-beads-lookup.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:36:05.553598-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21012","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Reproduction verified: Tested FallbackShowWithDir with cross-project lookup (specs-platform-28 from orch-go dir). Now returns ErrIssueNotFound instead of parse error. Tests pass: go test ./pkg/beads/... ./pkg/daemon/... - all passing.","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:41:53.998789-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21012","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added ErrIssueNotFound error type to pkg/beads/client.go and updated getClosedIssuesForProject to suppress warnings for expected 'not found' errors during cross-project lookups. Tests: go test ./pkg/beads/... ./pkg/daemon/... - all passing.","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:41:57.648846-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21013","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Verify OpenCode OAuth priority fix was lost: ch...","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T11:23:51.111084-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T17:43:01.166932-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-21014","title":"orch frontier reports stuck agents for closed issues","description":"Likely stuck detection/registry drift; should exclude closed issues and reconcile against workspace/opencode state.","repro":"1) Run ⚠️  HEALTH WARNINGS\n   1 stuck agents (\u003e 2h) - run 'orch clean --stale' to clean up\n\nREADY TO RELEASE (46)\n   [task] orch-go-20979  Investigate SSE reconnection in OpenCode c...\n   [feature] orch-go-20985  Auto-rebuild OpenCode binary when fork cha...\n   [bug] orch-go-20988  orch cannot inspect OpenCode sessions not ...\n   [feature] orch-go-21009  orchestrator skill: move behavioral guides...\n   [bug] orch-go-21010  daemon: rollback in_progress status when s...\n   [bug] orch-go-21012  orch spawn shows 'beads lookup failed' war...\n   [task] orch-go-21013  [orch-go] investigation: Verify OpenCode O...\n   [epic] orch-go-60vb1  Epic: Audit CLI error UX across orch ecosy...\n   ... and 38 more\n\nBLOCKED (2)\n   orch-go-kz7zr  Epic: Governance Infrastructure ...\n      ← blocked by: orch-go-ajxm1\n   orch-go-i3b5l  Update documentation for Docker ...\n      ← blocked by: orch-go-m3f8b\n\nACTIVE (2)\n   opencode-untracked-1769621244 [tmux] (feature-impl)\n   opencode-untracked-1769714652 [tmux] (investigation)\n\nSTUCK (\u003e 2h) (1)\n   orch-go-20997 [20h 41m] 2) Observe STUCK list includes orch-go-21008 + orch-go-20997 3) Run \norch-go-21008: skillc: add deployment headers to reference files\nStatus: closed\nPriority: P2\nType: feature\nCreated: 2026-01-29 09:56\nCreated by: dylanconlin\nUpdated: 2026-01-29 10:04\n\nDescription:\nReference files copied during skillc deploy lack the AUTO-GENERATED header that SKILL.md has. This makes the 'don't edit deployed files' contract invisible, leading to edits in ~/.claude/skills/ that get overwritten on next deploy.\n\n**Root cause:** Progressive disclosure design (Jan 2026) introduced reference/ directories for on-demand loading. The design focused on discovery mechanism (direct file paths) but didn't account for edit-time confusion.\n\n**Evidence:** Just hit this - edited ~/.claude/skills/meta/orchestrator/reference/model-selection.md instead of source at ~/orch-knowledge/skills/src/meta/orchestrator/reference/model-selection.md. Edit was overwritten on next deploy.\n\n**Proposed fix:** skillc deploy should add header to copied reference files:\n```\n\u003c!-- Deployed from: ~/orch-knowledge/skills/src/.../reference/... --\u003e\n\u003c!-- To modify: edit source file, then run: skillc deploy --\u003e\n```\n\n**Reference:** .kb/investigations/2026-01-17-inv-design-core-vs-reference-split.md\n\nLabels: [triage:ready]\n\nComments (4):\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-29 09:56]\n  Phase: Planning - Adding deployment headers to reference files to prevent edits in deployed location\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-29 09:59]\n  Scope: 1. Modify handleDeploy to detect reference/ directories 2. Add header generation for reference files 3. Copy reference/ dirs with headers during deployment 4. Test with actual skill deployment\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-29 09:59]\n  Phase: Implementing - Adding reference file copy logic with deployment headers to skillc\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-29 10:03]\n  Phase: Complete - Added deployment headers to reference files. Changes committed to skillc repo (commit 5177ba0). All reference files now show source path and modification instructions when deployed. and \norch-go-20997: Add version command to glass CLI\nStatus: closed\nPriority: P2\nType: task\nCreated: 2026-01-28 13:16\nCreated by: dylanconlin\nUpdated: 2026-01-29 11:02\n\nDescription:\nAdd 'glass version' and 'glass version --json' subcommand. Glass already has ldflags (Version, BuildTime, SourceDir, GitHash) - just needs ~30 lines to expose them. Follow orch version pattern. Enables orch doctor to verify glass binary staleness.\n\nLabels: [triage:ready]\n\nComments (9):\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 13:20]\n  Scope: 1. Add 'glass version' subcommand 2. Add 'glass version --json' flag support 3. Expose existing ldflags (Version, BuildTime, SourceDir, GitHash) 4. Follow orch version pattern\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 13:20]\n  Phase: Planning - Adding version command to glass CLI following orch version pattern\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 13:21]\n  QUESTION: Cannot locate glass CLI source code in orch-go repo. The task says 'glass already has ldflags' but I cannot find cmd/glass/, tools/glass/, or glass.go anywhere. Is glass in a separate repository? If so, what's the repo path?\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 13:23]\n  Phase: Implementation - Glass repo located at /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/glass, proceeding with version command implementation\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 13:24]\n  CONSTRAINT: Task requires modifying /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/glass/ (separate repo) but my workspace is /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go. This is cross-project work. Reverting unauthorized edits to glass/main.go. Need orchestrator guidance on spawn strategy (spawn in glass repo? --no-track?).\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 13:33]\n  Phase: Implementation - Working in glass repo at ~/Documents/personal/glass/, implementing version command with --json support\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 13:35]\n  IMPORTANT: Glass source is at ~/Documents/personal/glass/ (separate repo, not in orch-go)\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 15:47]\n  Phase: Planning - Adding version command to glass CLI following orch version pattern\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 15:47]\n  Scope: 1. Add 'glass version' command 2. Add 'glass version --json' support 3. Expose ldflags (Version, BuildTime, SourceDir, GitHash) 4. Follow orch version pattern and see both Status: closed 4) Run Issue orch-go-21008 is already closed in beads\nPhase: Complete\nSummary: Added deployment headers to reference files. Changes committed to skillc repo (commit 5177ba0). All reference files now show source path and modification instructions when deployed.\n\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  🔍 BEHAVIORAL VALIDATION SUGGESTED                         │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Type: concurrency\n│  Reason: File changes detected: concurrency\n│  ⚠️  No behavioral evidence found in beads comments\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Suggested validation steps:                                │\n│  1. Run the code with multiple concurrent requests\n│  2. Verify locks acquire and release correctly\n│  3. Check for race conditions\n│  4. Test timeout/retry behavior\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Changed files:                                             │\n│    .kb/decisions/2026-01-19-worker-authority-bound...\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\nReason: Added deployment headers to reference files. Changes committed to skillc repo (commit 5177ba0). All reference files now show source path and modification instructions when deployed.\n\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  ⚠️  NOTABLE ECOSYSTEM CHANGES DETECTED                      │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  📌 [kb-cli] feat: add blocks: frontmatter guidanc... \n│    (behavioral)\n│  📌 [orch-knowledge] feat: add blocks: frontmatter gui\n│    danc... (behavioral)\n│  📌 [orch-go] feat: add pre-spawn decision check so...\n│     (behavioral)\n│  📌 [orch-go] test: add tests for /api/kb-health en...\n│     (behavioral)\n│  📌 [agentlog] feat: add version command with --json..\n│    . (behavioral)\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Review recent changes that may affect agent behavior       │\n│  Run: orch changelog --days 3                               │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ and it succeeds","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:28:08.651169-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T12:34:44.837783-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T12:34:44.837783-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21014","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-orch-frontier-reports-stuck-agents.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:29:00.201105-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21014","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Adding beads status check to filter closed issues from stuck agent detection","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:29:47.955767-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21014","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Reproduction verified: Ran orch frontier after fix - closed issue orch-go-20997 no longer appears in STUCK section. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/ -run TestFilter -v - 5 passed, 0 failed","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:34:11.474567-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21014","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Fixed orch frontier stuck agent detection by filtering out agents for closed beads issues. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/ -run TestFilter -v - 5 passed, 0 failed. Commit: 31ef6e84","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:34:14.94555-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21015","title":"Orchestrator role signal: auto-enable only for orch sessions (not all chats)","description":"Decision kb-4eb82b: Add explicit orchestrator role signal (e.g., session metadata/instructions/CLAUDE_CONTEXT) when an 'orch session' is started so the agent behaves as orchestrator without manual prompting, but do not force orchestrator mode for every chat in orch-go root.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:35:13.029533-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T12:40:42.006073-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T12:40:42.006073-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21015","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Understanding session creation and orchestrator role signal implementation","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:36:12.66516-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21015","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Find/create 'orch session' command that starts orchestrator sessions 2. Add CLAUDE_CONTEXT/role signal when starting orchestrator session 3. Ensure signal only applies to 'orch session' (not all orch-go root chats) 4. Verify orchestrator skill auto-loads without manual prompting","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:36:45.998148-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21015","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Design - Creating session-context plugin that reads CLAUDE_CONTEXT env var to auto-load orchestrator skill for orchestrator sessions while skipping for workers (ORCH_WORKER=1)","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:38:31.780461-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21015","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Created .opencode/plugin/session-context.ts that reads CLAUDE_CONTEXT env var and injects orchestrator role signal for orchestrator/meta-orchestrator sessions while skipping for workers (ORCH_WORKER=1)","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:39:17.765824-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21015","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Delivered .opencode/plugin/session-context.ts that implements kb-4eb82b decision. Plugin reads CLAUDE_CONTEXT env var (already set by spawn/claude.go) and injects orchestrator role instructions for orchestrator/meta-orchestrator sessions via session.start hook. Skips for workers (ORCH_WORKER=1) and normal chats (unset CLAUDE_CONTEXT). Committed as a060e652.","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:39:37.908939-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21016","title":"[orch-go] investigation: OpenCode TUI mode switch (build/orchestrator/plan)","description":"User reports OpenCode TUI shows a mode indicator that cycles via Tab: build → orchestrator → plan. Need to determine what this actually does.\n\nQuestions to answer (with evidence):\n- Where is the mode implemented in Dylan's OpenCode fork (~/Documents/personal/opencode) and/or upstream?\n- Does switching mode change the system prompt/instructions sent to the model? Or just UI affordances?\n- Does it change tool availability, temperature/model selection, or message routing?\n- Is the mode persisted anywhere (session metadata, disk storage, SSE events)? Can orch-go observe it via API?\n\nDeliverables:\n- .kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-opencode-tui-mode-switch.md\n- If integration needed: create follow-up beads issue(s) with scoped implementation.\n\nScope:\n- IN: code inspection + minimal repro tests (e.g., log/trace prompt payloads if available)\n- OUT: implementing orch-go changes (file follow-up issue instead)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:37:42.85748-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T14:06:18.230691-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T14:06:18.230691-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21016","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating OpenCode TUI mode switch (build/orchestrator/plan) to determine implementation location and behavioral differences","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:38:43.547466-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21016","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Investigation - Found that 'mode' is deprecated field showing agent name. Tab cycles agents (build/plan/etc) via local.agent.move(). No separate mode system - just agent selection.","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:53:46.922348-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21016","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Investigation file created at .kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-opencode-tui-mode-switch.md. Key finding: 'mode' is deprecated field storing agent name. Tab cycles agents (build/plan/custom) via permissions, not separate mode system. Mode persisted in messages, observable via API.","created_at":"2026-01-29T14:05:35.278564-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21017","title":"OpenCode server (4096) dies; orch doctor --fix can't bring it up","description":"Observed during `orch complete orch-go-21015`: completion could not fetch/export/delete OpenCode session messages because OpenCode API (127.0.0.1:4096) refused connections. `orch doctor --fix` also fails to bring OpenCode up; it reports \"OpenCode started but not responding after 10s\".\n\nRepro:\n1) Run `orch doctor`\n2) Observe: OpenCode (port 4096) Not responding\n3) Run `orch doctor --fix`\n4) Observe: Failed to start OpenCode: started but not responding after 10s\n5) Run `curl -m 2 http://127.0.0.1:4096/session`\n6) Observe: connect refused / cannot connect\n\nImpact:\n- orch complete cannot export activity or delete sessions\n- dashboard `/api/agents` returns 500 when OpenCode is down\n\nSuspect:\n- opencode process spawned via overmind/servers exits immediately (PID reported but gone)","repro":"1) Run orch doctor - Service Health Check\n===================================\n\n✓ orch binary\n  UP TO DATE\n✗ OpenCode (port 4096)\n  Not responding\n✓ orch serve (port 3348)\n  Health OK, /api/agents status 500\n✗ Web UI (port 5188)\n  Not listening\n✓ Overmind (launchd)\n  Running (PID 59329)\n✗ Beads Daemon\n  Not running (optional)\n✓ Session Health\n  No active sessions\n✓ Beads DB Integrity\n  Database integrity verified\n✗ Registry Reconciliation\n  ⚠️ 253 stale registry entries (tmux windows missing)\n✓ Docker Backend\n  Container test passed (Docker 28.4.0)\n\nSome services are not running.\n\nSome services are not running. Use 'orch doctor --fix' to start them. (or orch doctor - Service Health Check\n===================================\n\n✓ orch binary\n  UP TO DATE\n✗ OpenCode (port 4096)\n  Not responding\n✓ orch serve (port 3348)\n  Health OK, /api/agents status 500\n✗ Web UI (port 5188)\n  Not listening\n✓ Overmind (launchd)\n  Running (PID 59329)\n✗ Beads Daemon\n  Not running (optional)\n✓ Session Health\n  No active sessions\n✓ Beads DB Integrity\n  Database integrity verified\n✗ Registry Reconciliation\n  ⚠️ 253 stale registry entries (tmux windows missing)\n✓ Docker Backend\n  Container test passed (Docker 28.4.0)\n\nSome services are not running.\n\nAttempting to fix issues...\n\nStarting OpenCode...\n  ❌ Failed to start OpenCode: OpenCode started but not responding after 10s) 2) Observe OpenCode (port 4096) Not responding 3) orch doctor - Service Health Check\n===================================\n\n✓ orch binary\n  UP TO DATE\n✗ OpenCode (port 4096)\n  Not responding\n✓ orch serve (port 3348)\n  Health OK, /api/agents status 500\n✗ Web UI (port 5188)\n  Not listening\n✓ Overmind (launchd)\n  Running (PID 59329)\n✗ Beads Daemon\n  Not running (optional)\n✓ Session Health\n  No active sessions\n✓ Beads DB Integrity\n  Database integrity verified\n✗ Registry Reconciliation\n  ⚠️ 253 stale registry entries (tmux windows missing)\n✓ Docker Backend\n  Container test passed (Docker 28.4.0)\n\nSome services are not running.\n\nAttempting to fix issues...\n\nStarting OpenCode...\n  ❌ Failed to start OpenCode: OpenCode started but not responding after 10s prints 'OpenCode started but not responding after 10s' 4)  fails to connect","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:43:13.974455-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T12:44:12.799668-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T12:44:12.799668-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-21018","title":"orch-go dashboard web server start command is stale (bun script dev missing)","description":"The servers window shows a bun command that no longer exists in package scripts, so the web UI can't be started from the standard workflow. Fix the servers command (tmuxinator/workers config or whatever `orch-dashboard restart` uses) to the current correct start command.","repro":"1) Attach to `workers-orch-go:servers`\n2) Run the dashboard web start command shown there (currently `bun run dev --port 5188`)\n3) Observe: `error: Script not found \"dev\"`\n4) As a result, Web UI on 5188 is not listening","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:43:42.097828-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T13:44:07.26473-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T13:44:07.26473-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21018","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating web UI start command drift","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:38:15.848862-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21018","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Found root cause: tmuxinator generator creates 'bun run dev --port N' but should use Procfile commands. Fixing generator to parse Procfile when available.","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:40:41.222325-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21018","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Fixed tmuxinator generator to read Procfile commands when available, falling back to auto-generated commands. The orch-go tmuxinator config now correctly uses 'orch serve' and 'cd web \u0026\u0026 bun run dev' from Procfile. Tests: go test ./pkg/tmux/... - 37 passed, 0 failed. Verified orch-dashboard restart works correctly.","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:43:20.363607-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21019","title":"OpenCode server on 4096 not responding; orch doctor --fix can't recover","description":"Observed while completing orch-go-21015: orch complete could not fetch/export/delete OpenCode session messages because 4096 refused connections. Overmind/dashboard restart reports opencode PID but process exits quickly (PID not alive right after).","repro":"1) Run: orch doctor\n2) Observe: OpenCode (port 4096) Not responding\n3) Run: orch doctor --fix\n4) Observe: Failed to start OpenCode (started but not responding after 10s)\n5) Run: curl -m 2 http://127.0.0.1:4096/session\n6) Observe: cannot connect / connection refused","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:44:07.563147-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T13:36:38.280866-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T13:36:38.280866-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21019","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating OpenCode server 4096 crash issue, reviewing existing investigations and server startup","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:44:35.571119-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21019","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-opencode-server-4096-not-responding.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:45:00.464613-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21019","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating dashboard startup failures (opencode/api/web dying immediately)","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:50:58.949714-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21019","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Reproduction verified: Missing web/node_modules caused vite command not found. After bun install, orch-dashboard restart succeeds with all services (api/web/opencode) responding on ports 3348/5188/4096.","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:52:43.340823-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21019","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Root cause: missing web/node_modules. Fix: bun install in web/. Tests: curl health checks - 200 OK on all three ports (3348/5188/4096). No code changes needed - operational fix only.","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:52:56.469312-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21020","title":"Run GPT-5.2 modal orchestrator experiment","description":"Execute the 5-scenario test protocol from . Capture pass/fail per scenario + notes on permission-denial UX, gate handling, and role-boundary adherence. Outcome: propose decision update/new decision distinguishing orchestrator vs worker model requirements.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:54:50.151296-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T13:59:08.784718-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T13:59:08.784718-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21020","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Setting up GPT-5.2 modal orchestrator experiment","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:56:07.322228-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21020","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Execute 5-scenario test protocol (Multi-Gate Spawn, Role Boundary, Failure Adaptation, Deliberation Control, Instruction Synthesis) 2. Capture pass/fail per scenario 3. Document permission-denial UX 4. Document gate handling behavior 5. Document role-boundary adherence 6. Propose decision update/new decision for orchestrator vs worker model requirements","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:56:21.014702-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21020","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Setting up test prerequisites (backup config, create modal agent config)","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:56:36.515643-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21020","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Testing - Running Scenario 1: Multi-Gate Spawn","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:57:24.224495-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21020","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added GPT-5.2 modal orchestrator agent config to .opencode/opencode.json. Changes: (1) New agent named gpt_orchestrator with model openai/gpt-5.2, mode primary, temp 0.3, steps 50. (2) Safe permissions: deny edit/write/notebookedit, allow only orch/bd/kb/git read-only commands, read limited to .kb/.orch/CLAUDE.md/*.md. (3) Preserved existing permission.task = deny. (4) Backup saved to .opencode/opencode.json.bak. To run test scenarios: opencode --agent gpt_orchestrator. Test protocol and results template in .kb/investigations/2026-01-29-gpt-orchestrator-modal-test-results.md with 5 scenarios ready to execute.","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:58:58.812893-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21021","title":"[orch-go] issue-creation: Dashboard Strategic Center appears incomplete/e...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:58:43.831138-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T20:34:25.185675-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T20:34:25.185675-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21021","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating dashboard Strategic Center incomplete/empty sections","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:59:03.299926-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21021","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Investigation - Found root cause: field name mismatches between kb-health API response and UI component expectations. Synthesis items: API returns 'count' but UI expects 'investigation_count', missing 'oldest_days'. Stale items: API returns 'age_days' but UI expects 'days_old'. Investigation promotions: API returns 'suggestion' but UI expects 'recommendation'. Creating bug now.","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:17:08.270201-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21021","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Creating Issue - Writing bug report with P-S-E structure including reproduction steps and file references","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:17:19.176986-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21021","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Created bug orch-go-21033 (field-name mismatches between /api/kb-health and decision-center.svelte expectations) and applied triage label.","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:33:28.814623-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21022","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Investigate Strategic Center dashboard implemen...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T14:20:57.909748-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T17:44:20.959488-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T17:44:20.959488-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-21023","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Investigate Strategic Center dashboard implemen...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T14:21:10.13652-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T10:24:41.659763-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T10:24:41.659763-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21023","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating Strategic Center dashboard implementation completeness","created_at":"2026-01-29T14:21:23.772922-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21023","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-investigate-strategic-center-dashboard-implementation.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T14:21:32.185385-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21023","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Strategic Center implementation is COMPLETE and working as designed. The 'incomplete' appearance is intentional UX: empty categories (Absorb Knowledge, Give Approvals, Handle Failures) are hidden by design to reduce visual noise. Current data (1 question, 15 knowledge items) reflects actual system state. Investigation file: .kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-investigate-strategic-center-dashboard-implementation.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T14:24:20.277084-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21024","title":"Dashboard follow mode doesn't show daemon-spawned cross-project agents","description":"Agents spawned by daemon for cross-project work don't appear in dashboard when following that project's context. They only appear when following orch-go (the daemon's home).\n\nSuspect: Agent project detection uses session directory or spawn origin rather than the --workdir passed to the agent.\n\nRelated: .kb/models/cross-project-visibility.md","repro":"1. Enable cross-project daemon (--cross-project flag)\n2. Have dashboard running with follow mode enabled\n3. Daemon spawns agent for specs-platform (e.g., specs-platform-29)\n4. Switch orchestrator tmux window to specs-platform project\n5. Dashboard filters to specs-platform context\n6. Observe: daemon-spawned specs-platform agents NOT visible\n7. Switch orchestrator window back to orch-go\n8. Observe: specs-platform agents now visible (wrong project context)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T16:35:23.055484-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T18:18:21.34665-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T18:18:21.34665-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21024","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating dashboard follow mode bug where daemon-spawned cross-project agents don't appear in project dashboard","created_at":"2026-01-29T18:04:51.937088-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21024","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-dashboard-follow-mode-doesn-show.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T18:05:01.277045-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21024","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Fixed cross-project agent visibility bug in dashboard follow mode.\n\nRoot cause: Workspace cache parsing allowed template placeholders (\u003cbeads-id\u003e) to overwrite the correct beads ID extracted from the authoritative 'spawned from beads issue' line.\n\nFixes applied:\n1. Only extract beads ID on first match (first-match-wins)\n2. Add Project field extraction for completed workspaces\n3. Added regression test\n\nFiles: serve_agents_cache.go, serve_agents.go, serve_agents_test.go\nInvestigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-dashboard-follow-mode-doesn-show.md\n\nTests pass. Changes pushed to origin/master.","created_at":"2026-01-29T18:17:42.917272-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21025","title":"orch frontier disagrees with orch status/daemon spawn (active agents + skill mismatch)","repro":"1) Label any issue triage:ready\n2) Run: orch daemon once (note printed Skill)\n3) Run: orch frontier (note active agent skill)\n4) Run: orch status (often reports 'No active agents')\nObserved example: daemon spawned orch-go-21012 as systematic-debugging, but frontier shows orch-go-21012 as (architect)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:35:06.147317-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T19:41:01.122756-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T19:41:01.122756-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21025","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating orch frontier disagreement with orch status/daemon spawn regarding active agents and skill mismatch","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:35:25.700244-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21025","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-orch-frontier-disagrees-orch-status.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:35:58.008105-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21025","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Fixed skill inference inconsistency between daemon and work command. Both now use systematic-debugging for bugs (per decision 2026-01-23). Build passes, tests pass.","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:38:38.315815-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21025","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/... ./pkg/daemon/... -run Skill - all 50+ skill-related tests passing. Fixed skill inference inconsistency between daemon (systematic-debugging for bugs) and spawn command (was architect, now systematic-debugging). Root cause was two separate inference functions with conflicting mappings. Investigation and fix committed.","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:40:37.518234-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21026","title":"Reduce cross-project beads lookups using session.Directory","description":"Follow-up from orch-go-21012: today we suppress expected 'issue not found' errors, but we can avoid the lookup entirely.\n\nIdea: in spawn/daemon closed-issue scanning (spawn_concurrency or equivalent), use OpenCode session.Directory (x-opencode-directory) / project detection to query the correct beads DB for that session when determining whether an issue is closed.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:45:41.190931-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T19:56:26.008103-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T19:56:26.008103-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21026","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating spawn/daemon closed-issue scanning to use session.Directory for targeted beads lookups","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:53:04.02963-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21026","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Update spawn_concurrency.go to collect session.Directory from OpenCode sessions 2. Pass session directories to GetClosedIssuesBatchWithProjectDirs instead of GetClosedIssuesBatch 3. This avoids cross-project lookup failures that are currently suppressed","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:53:27.846702-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21026","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Updating spawn_concurrency.go to use session.Directory","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:53:41.287907-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21026","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Updated spawn_concurrency.go to use session.Directory for targeted beads lookups, avoiding cross-project lookup failures. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch -run TestCheckConcurrency - PASS, go test ./pkg/daemon - 213 passed, 0 failed (4.030s). Leave it Better: Created kb decision kb-7c6001 documenting pattern.","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:55:59.14062-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21027","title":"Investigate bd CLI: 'bd show \u003cid\u003e --json' returns exit code 0 with empty stdout for not-found","description":"Follow-up from orch-go-21012 investigation. Observed in orch-go repo: running 'bd show specs-platform-28 --json' returns exit code 0 with empty stdout (error on stderr). This makes callers think JSON parse failed.\n\nGoal: decide whether to fix beads CLI to exit non-zero or emit valid JSON error payload, or document/standardize empty-stdout behavior.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:45:41.249884-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T21:08:45.768724-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T21:08:45.768724-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21027","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating bd CLI exit code behavior for not-found IDs","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:05:26.158609-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21027","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Test current behavior of 'bd show \u003cid\u003e --json' for not-found IDs 2. Analyze exit codes and output patterns 3. Review beads CLI implementation 4. Decide on fix approach (exit non-zero vs JSON error payload vs document behavior)","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:05:28.096954-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21027","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Investigation - Treating as investigation-only per orchestrator correction. No code changes.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:05:43.09446-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21027","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Investigation complete. Reproduced issue: bd show exits 0 with empty stdout for not-found IDs. Root cause: multi-ID continue-on-error pattern bypasses exit signaling. Filed upstream bug bd-85487069 in beads repo with recommended fix (hybrid: fail fast for single ID, exit 1 if ANY multi-ID fails). No orch-go changes needed - upstream beads CLI issue. Investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-bd-cli-show-exit-code-not-found.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:08:05.713461-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21028","title":"Decide default visibility for untracked OpenCode sessions in orch status","description":"Follow-up from orch-go-20988: we now show untracked sessions under 'orch status --all' as STATUS=untracked.\n\nOpen question: should untracked sessions be shown by default (no --all) to improve reliability/visibility, or would that add noise?","notes":"Reset to open after abandoned spawn","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:45:41.308697-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T12:55:48.648325-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T12:55:48.648325-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21028","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Analyzing current orch status behavior for untracked sessions","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:56:51.756727-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21028","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Analysis - Reviewing current behavior and trade-offs. With --all flag, found 1 untracked session with 224K tokens in CRITICAL state - this visibility is operationally important for orchestrators.","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:58:08.531227-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21028","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Analyzing default visibility for untracked OpenCode sessions","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:41:29.810818-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21028","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating current status command behavior and untracked session handling","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:48:52.121838-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21028","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Analyze current untracked session visibility behavior 2. Evaluate trade-offs (visibility/reliability vs noise) 3. Make recommendation on default visibility 4. Implement if code change needed","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:50:27.813111-08:00"},{"id":6,"issue_id":"orch-go-21028","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Analysis - Current behavior is inconsistent: swarm shows 'Untracked: 1' but agents hidden by default. Found 1 untracked session with 2h20m runtime, 27K output tokens - operationally significant. Recommendation: show by default for consistency and resource visibility.","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:50:52.022028-08:00"},{"id":7,"issue_id":"orch-go-21028","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Removing filter that hides untracked sessions by default (lines 528-534)","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:51:05.303463-08:00"},{"id":8,"issue_id":"orch-go-21028","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Validation - Tested successfully. Default status now shows untracked session (ses_3efd4c73... with 2h22m runtime, opus model). Also shows correctly with --all (5 total agents including 1 untracked, 2 completed).","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:53:01.960637-08:00"},{"id":9,"issue_id":"orch-go-21028","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Implemented default visibility for untracked sessions. Changes: 1) Removed untracked filter from status display 2) Exempted untracked from compact mode 3) Updated status guide. Tests: manual verification - default status shows untracked session (ses_3efd4c73..., 2h22m, opus), --all shows all 6 agents. Commits: 3ad71d71, 9b522c6e","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:54:25.926666-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21029","title":"Add workflow to claim/adopt untracked OpenCode sessions into beads tracking","description":"Follow-up from orch-go-20988. Now that untracked sessions are visible, provide a way to associate a session (ses_xxx) with a beads issue/workspace so orch tooling can manage it (tail/status/complete/cleanup) without starting over.","notes":"Reset to open after abandoned spawn","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:45:41.366689-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T21:55:01.970156-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T21:55:01.970156-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21029","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Adding workflow to claim untracked OpenCode sessions into beads tracking","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:47:21.202856-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21029","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Design - Analyzed session tracking architecture. Sessions tracked via BeadsID↔Workspace↔SessionID linkage. Will add 'orch sessions claim' command to create workspace+manifest for untracked sessions.","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:48:07.324871-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21029","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Adding workflow to claim/adopt untracked OpenCode sessions into beads tracking","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:01:30.439423-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21029","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Add workflow to claim/adopt untracked OpenCode sessions (ses_xxx) 2. Associate sessions with beads issue/workspace 3. Enable orch tooling (tail/status/complete/cleanup) to manage claimed sessions 4. Build on orch-go-20988 (untracked sessions visibility)","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:01:32.559038-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21029","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Design - Claim workflow will create workspace for untracked session, enabling orch tooling (tail/complete/cleanup) via beads ID lookup. No need to update session title - workspace is sufficient.","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:03:19.219997-08:00"},{"id":6,"issue_id":"orch-go-21029","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Add claim workflow for untracked sessions 2. Associate ses_xxx with beads issue/workspace 3. Enable orch tooling (tail/status/complete/cleanup) for claimed sessions","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:41:23.026268-08:00"},{"id":7,"issue_id":"orch-go-21029","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating codebase to understand untracked sessions and claim workflow integration points","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:41:24.115164-08:00"},{"id":8,"issue_id":"orch-go-21029","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Design - Design approach: Add 'orch claim' command to create workspace + files (.session_id, .beads_id, AGENT_MANIFEST.json) for untracked session. This enables full orch tooling (tail/status/complete) via beads ID lookup without modifying session title.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:45:15.016262-08:00"},{"id":9,"issue_id":"orch-go-21029","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Design complete at docs/designs/2026-01-29-session-claim-workflow.md. Starting implementation of 'orch claim' command.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:46:54.270111-08:00"},{"id":10,"issue_id":"orch-go-21029","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added 'orch claim' command (cmd/orch/claim_cmd.go) to associate untracked OpenCode sessions with beads issues. Creates workspace with all required files (.session_id, .beads_id, AGENT_MANIFEST.json). Enables orch tail/complete/cleanup via beads ID. Includes tests. Committed: a99be5e0","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:54:42.601277-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21030","title":"Benchmark orch status performance with large OpenCode session counts","description":"Follow-up from orch-go-20988: status now does extra work to detect/display untracked sessions. Need to validate performance with 100s+ sessions (in-memory + disk) and ensure --all doesn't become slow.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:45:41.424568-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T13:01:59.586647-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T13:01:59.586647-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21030","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Benchmarking orch status performance with large session counts","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:47:46.008347-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21030","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Benchmark status with 100+ OpenCode sessions (in-memory) 2. Benchmark status --all with large disk session count 3. Measure performance impact of untracked session detection 4. Verify no regression from orch-go-20988 changes 5. Document performance characteristics and recommend optimizations if needed","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:48:03.246332-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21030","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Benchmarking orch status with 100s+ sessions to validate performance after untracked session detection changes","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:01:52.003044-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21030","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Create benchmark tool to generate 100s+ OpenCode sessions (in-memory + disk). 2. Benchmark 'orch status' performance (compact mode). 3. Benchmark 'orch status --all' performance. 4. Profile performance bottlenecks in session discovery phases. 5. Validate untracked session detection performance. 6. Document findings and recommend optimizations if needed.","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:02:19.179162-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21030","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Benchmarking orch status performance with large session counts","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:52:34.164303-08:00"},{"id":6,"issue_id":"orch-go-21030","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Create benchmark to simulate 100s+ OpenCode sessions 2. Measure orch status performance with large session counts 3. Test both in-memory (actual sessions) and disk (registry) scenarios 4. Validate --all flag performance 5. Ensure untracked session detection (from orch-go-20988) doesn't cause slowdown","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:53:25.162799-08:00"},{"id":7,"issue_id":"orch-go-21030","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Creating benchmark tests with mock OpenCode API server to test 100s+ sessions","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:54:21.689721-08:00"},{"id":8,"issue_id":"orch-go-21030","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Testing - Initial benchmarks show ~500ms constant performance (100-1000 sessions). Adding latency simulation for realistic testing.","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:57:16.079563-08:00"},{"id":9,"issue_id":"orch-go-21030","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Created comprehensive benchmark suite (cmd/orch/status_bench_test.go) testing 100-1000 sessions with configurable latency. Key finding: 1000 sessions = 2.1s with realistic latency (O(n) complexity, ~1 API call/session). Untracked session detection (orch-go-20988) has no significant perf impact. Full analysis: docs/benchmark-orch-status-performance.md. Tests: go test -bench=BenchmarkStatus ./cmd/orch/ - 8 benchmarks pass.","created_at":"2026-01-30T13:01:02.043581-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21031","title":"Harden orch-dashboard restart when OpenCode already running on 4096","description":"Goal: orch-dashboard restart should be resilient when 4096 is already bound.\n\nExpected behavior options (pick safest):\n- Detect existing listener on 4096 and either (a) reuse it (skip starting Procfile opencode) OR (b) stop it explicitly before starting overmind.\n- Overmind should not kill api/web just because opencode failed to bind (mark opencode as can-die or implement conditional start).\n\nAcceptance:\n- orch-dashboard restart results in api + web up even if opencode already running\n- clear log message explaining whether opencode was reused or restarted\n- no orphaned .overmind.sock / misleading 'dead' statuses\n\nNotes:\n- Procfile currently defines opencode: env -u ANTHROPIC_API_KEY ~/.bun/bin/opencode serve --port 4096","repro":"1) Start OpenCode manually: opencode serve --port 4096 (or have it running already)\n2) In orch-go repo: orch-dashboard restart\n3) Observe overmind starts, then all processes show dead; opencode reports failed to start server on port 4096; api/web die with it; .overmind.sock disappears; overmind echo/ps unusable","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:51:40.803656-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T13:30:47.635063-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T13:30:47.635063-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21031","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating orch-dashboard restart resilience when port 4096 is already bound","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:52:31.801916-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21031","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Testing restart without opencode running. Fixed timing issue where temp Procfile was deleted before overmind read it. Restart with existing opencode verified working.","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:03:16.685749-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21031","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating orch-dashboard restart resilience when port 4096 is already bound","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:06:11.008186-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21031","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Fix implemented and initial test passed. Verifying services are running correctly after deploy.","created_at":"2026-01-30T13:28:52.251981-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21031","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Hardened orch deploy to handle port 4096 already in use. Tests: go build ./cmd/orch/... - builds successfully. Smoke test: ran orch deploy with opencode already on 4096 - api+web started successfully, opencode reused.","created_at":"2026-01-30T13:29:46.369731-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21032","title":"Auto-resume agents after OpenCode/server restart (lost sessions stay in_progress)","description":"Reliability: server restarts are expected; active work should recover.\n\nAcceptance:\n- Detect when OpenCode restart kills active orch-tracked sessions\n- Automatically resume work (spawn new session) or mark issues back to open with a clear 'killed by restart' reason + suggested next action\n- Avoid silent loss: emit a clear event in dashboard/agentlog\n\nRelated:\n- Repro observed today: orch-go-21030, orch-go-20985, orch-go-21029 were killed by server restart and did not resume","repro":"1) Spawn 2-3 agents (e.g., orch-go-21030, orch-go-20985, orch-go-21029)\n2) Restart OpenCode via orch-dashboard restart (kills port 4096) or otherwise restart server\n3) Observe: those agent sessions die/vanish, but orch does not automatically resume/re-spawn them\n4) Issues remain status=in_progress without active agent; work is stranded until manual intervention","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:00:05.411977-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T13:30:46.694963-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T13:30:46.694963-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21032","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Analyzing auto-resume mechanism for agents killed by server restart","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:01:03.406318-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21032","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Root cause identified: FindOrphanedSessions only looks for in_progress issues, but agents killed early remain in open status. Also spawned_tracker TTL blocks re-spawning. Fixing both issues.","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:07:40.628541-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21032","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating auto-resume mechanism for agents killed by server restart","created_at":"2026-01-30T13:25:27.866355-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21032","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Found root cause: FindOrphanedSessions matches workspace by directory name containing beadsID, but workspace names use short IDs (e.g., 'og-feat-xxx-29jan-6701') not full beads IDs (e.g., 'orch-go-20985'). Fix: read .beads_id file from each workspace to match correctly.","created_at":"2026-01-30T13:27:32.903676-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21032","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Fixed FindOrphanedSessions to read .beads_id file from workspace directories instead of matching directory names. Root cause: workspace names (e.g., 'og-feat-auto-rebuild-29jan-6701') don't contain full beads IDs (e.g., 'orch-go-20985'). Added ReadBeadsID() function. Tests: go test ./pkg/daemon/... - PASS, ./pkg/spawn builds. Smoke-tested with real workspace data.","created_at":"2026-01-30T13:30:13.594284-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21033","title":"Dashboard Strategic Center shows nonzero counts but panels/lists are empty","description":"## Problem\n\nThe Strategic Center dashboard panel displays nonzero badge counts (total: 15) indicating knowledge hygiene items require attention, but when expanded, all list items within the Tend Knowledge subsections appear empty/blank. Users see category headers with counts but no actionable item details.\n\nThis breaks the core purpose of the Strategic Center: surfacing knowledge hygiene opportunities that need human attention.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Root Cause:** Field name mismatches between API response schema and UI component expectations.\n\n**File References:**\n- `cmd/orch/serve_kb_health.go:13-22` - API returns KBHealthResponse with specific field names\n- `web/src/lib/components/decision-center/decision-center.svelte:230-238` - Synthesis UI expects `investigation_count` and `oldest_days`\n- `web/src/lib/components/decision-center/decision-center.svelte:260-268` - Stale UI expects `days_old`\n- `web/src/lib/components/decision-center/decision-center.svelte:277-285` - Investigation promotions UI expects `recommendation`\n\n**API Response (verified):**\n```json\n{\n  \"synthesis\": {\n    \"items\": [{\"topic\": \"feature\", \"count\": 5, \"investigations\": [...], \"suggestion\": \"...\"}]\n  },\n  \"stale\": {\n    \"items\": [{\"title\": \"...\", \"age_days\": 15, \"file\": \"...\", \"suggestion\": \"...\"}]\n  },\n  \"investigation_promotion\": {\n    \"items\": [{\"title\": \"...\", \"age_days\": 23, \"suggestion\": \"...\"}]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**UI Expectations (mismatched):**\n- Synthesis items: expects `investigation_count` (API provides `count`), expects `oldest_days` (API provides nothing)\n- Stale items: expects `days_old` (API provides `age_days`)\n- Investigation promotions: expects `recommendation` (API provides `suggestion`)\n\n**Reproduction:**\nConfirmed on local instance - Strategic Center badge shows 15, but Tend Knowledge subsections render empty divs.\n\n## Context\n\n**Impact:** High - Strategic Center is the primary interface for knowledge hygiene workflows. Users cannot see what actions are needed despite counts indicating work exists.\n\n**Failure Stage:** UI rendering layer. kb reflect → Go API works correctly, but Go-to-TypeScript schema mismatch causes UI rendering to fail silently (no errors, just empty display).\n\n**Related:** This is a data pipeline integrity issue similar to the null/stale handling fixed in Jan 7 dashboard work (see .kb/guides/dashboard.md lines 190-206).","repro":"1. Visit http://localhost:5188 2. Observe Strategic Center badge shows '15' total 3. Expand Strategic Center section 4. Observe: Tend Knowledge panel shows (5) synthesis, (5) stale, (5) investigation promotions but all list items are empty/blank 5. Check API: curl -k https://localhost:3348/api/kb-health shows data 6. Expected: List items should display with topic, age, and action details","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:17:44.830864-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T20:22:45.654684-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T20:22:45.654684-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21033","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Analyzing field name mismatches between API response schema and UI component expectations","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:18:25.723099-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21033","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Reproduction verified: Strategic Center Tend Knowledge panel now shows 5 synthesis items (feature, rebuild, reflection, untracked, quick), 5 stale decisions, and 5 investigation promotions with correct field mappings. Verified via dashboard screenshot at http://localhost:5188 in Ops view.","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:22:33.53617-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21033","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Fixed field name mismatches in decision-center.svelte: synthesis items use 'count' instead of 'investigation_count', stale items use 'age_days' instead of 'days_old', investigation promotions use 'suggestion' instead of 'recommendation'. Tests: npm run build - Svelte build succeeded. Pre-existing Go spawn test failures are unrelated (undefined functions in test file, not in changed code).","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:22:39.044802-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21034","title":"Investigate: which server restarts strand workers (:4096 vs :3348)?","description":"We see stuck workers after 'server crashes/restarts' but Dylan is unsure which server is actually restarting. Determine whether stranded workers correlate to OpenCode server (:4096) restarts (SSE stream drops → agent exits) vs orch serve (:3348) restarts (dashboard/API only). Correlate evidence from launchd logs, ~/.local/share/opencode/crash.log, ~/.orch/daemon.log, and any orch server logs with timestamps of agent stalls; conclude which process is primary and where restart-aware auto-resume detection should hook. Related: .kb/investigations/2026-01-17-inv-design-auto-resume-mechanism-stalled.md, .kb/investigations/2026-01-26-inv-opencode-server-keeps-crashing-dying.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","resolution_type":"factual","created_at":"2026-01-29T20:58:28.115498-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T21:16:44.853878-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T21:16:44.853878-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21034","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating which server restarts (:4096 vs :3348) correlate with stranded workers","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:05:03.278855-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21034","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating server restart impact on strand workers (ports 4096 vs 3348)","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:05:08.846967-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21034","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1) Check launchd logs for OpenCode (:4096) and orch serve (:3348) restarts 2) Check crash.log and daemon.log 3) Correlate timestamps with agent stalls 4) Determine primary cause 5) Recommend detection hook location","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:05:18.121279-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21034","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-server-restarts-strand-workers-4096.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:05:42.719529-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21034","author":"dylanconlin","text":"STOPPING: Wrong skill spawned (feature-impl for investigation task). Key finding: OpenCode :4096 restarts strand workers (multiple detected in logs). orch serve :3348 shows NO connection issues. Auto-resume already implemented in recovery.go. Issue 21032 fixing bug where 'open' status agents weren't resumed.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:07:27.687626-08:00"},{"id":6,"issue_id":"orch-go-21034","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Investigation determined OpenCode :4096 restarts historically stranded workers (SSE break), but SSE reconnection fix (Jan 28) should prevent this; orch serve :3348 restarts proven harmless via live test. Recommendations: make SSE fix permanent (orch-go-21036), add reconnection monitoring (orch-go-21037). Investigation file: .kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-server-restarts-strand-workers-4096.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:14:38.453731-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21035","title":"Daemon cannot spawn issues of type 'question' (orch work unknown issue type)","description":"This blocks using question issues as first-class spawns. Daemon tries to spawn but fails: 'cannot work on issue \u003cid\u003e: unknown issue type: question'. Expected: questions should map to investigation skill (or at least be spawnable via orch work). Impact: triage:ready questions starve the daemon and confuse users. Evidence: orch logs daemon shows failures for orch-go-21027 and orch-go-21034.","repro":"1) bd create --type question -l triage:ready \"Test question\" 2) Wait for daemon to spawn 3) Observe daemon log: cannot work on issue ... unknown issue type: question","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:05:07.268661-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T21:09:49.152064-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T21:09:49.152064-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21035","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating why daemon cannot spawn issues of type 'question'","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:05:35.613872-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21035","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Root cause: InferSkillFromIssueType in spawn_skill_inference.go was missing 'question' case. Fix: Added case for 'question' that maps to 'investigation' skill (matching daemon's InferSkill function and the help text documentation). Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/... -run TestInferSkillFromIssueType - 8 passed, 0 failed. Smoke-test: orch work orch-go-m3f8b successfully infers skill 'investigation' for type 'question'.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:08:46.714753-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21036","title":"Make SSE reconnection fix permanent in OpenCode SDK build","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:13:16.014927-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T21:17:48.017418-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T21:17:48.017418-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21036","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Add post-processing step to packages/sdk/js/script/build.ts to fix SSE reconnection after SDK generation 2. Ensure fix converts unconditional break to conditional break (if signal.aborted) at serverSentEvents.gen.ts:220 3. Test that fix persists after SDK regeneration 4. Verify reconnection works with test-sse-reconnect.sh","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:14:38.589937-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21036","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Adding post-processing step to build.ts to make SSE reconnection fix permanent","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:14:53.515365-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21036","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added post-processing step to opencode/packages/sdk/js/script/build.ts that automatically applies SSE reconnection fix after SDK generation. Fix converts unconditional break to conditional 'if (signal.aborted) break', enabling automatic reconnection when server restarts. \n\nTests: Verified fix persists after SDK rebuild - grep confirms 'Only exit retry loop' comment present after regeneration.\n\nEvidence: Prior investigation (2026-01-28) confirmed client (PID 78918) survived server kill/restart with this fix applied.\n\nCommitted: opencode@0ed6b1128 - fix(sdk): make SSE reconnection fix permanent in build process","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:17:30.51038-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21037","title":"Add SSE reconnection health monitoring","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:13:16.600978-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T21:20:55.817999-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T21:20:55.817999-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21037","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Reading SSE reconnection context and enumerating scope","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:14:45.625672-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21037","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Make SSE reconnection fix permanent via post-processing in packages/sdk/js/script/build.ts (prevent SDK regeneration from overwriting the fix) 2. Add health monitoring/logging for SSE reconnection events (track success/failure) 3. Test SDK regeneration to verify fix persists","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:15:12.101317-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21037","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Investigation - Build.ts already has post-processing fix (lines 43-53), but regex doesn't match current generated code. Line 220 has comment after break that prevents regex from matching. Need to fix regex pattern.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:15:50.77454-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21037","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Design - SSE reconnection fix is already permanent. SDK has onSseError callback for monitoring errors. Need to add comprehensive logging for: 1) connection established 2) reconnection attempts 3) reconnection success 4) max retry exhaustion. Will implement via post-processing to add logs to generated code.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:17:05.687189-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21037","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Adding SSE reconnection health monitoring to pkg/events/logger.go and pkg/opencode/monitor.go. Will track: 1) connection established 2) connection lost 3) reconnection attempts 4) reconnection success 5) reconnection failures. Events will be logged to ~/.orch/events.jsonl for health analysis.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:17:59.916242-08:00"},{"id":6,"issue_id":"orch-go-21037","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added SSE reconnection health monitoring with comprehensive event logging. Tests: go test ./pkg/events/ ./pkg/opencode/ - all passed (0.278s total). Deliverables: 1) Event types for SSE connection lifecycle (connection_established, connection_lost, reconnection_attempt, reconnection_success) 2) Logging methods in pkg/events/logger.go 3) Integration with Monitor in pkg/opencode/monitor.go 4) Full test coverage. Events logged to ~/.orch/events.jsonl for health analysis. Leave it Better: kb quick decide kb-a2e20f documenting implementation choice.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:20:31.479204-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21038","title":"Synthesize opencode/cli investigations into kb","description":"Refresh synthesis for opencode/cli: incorporate investigations since 2026-01-08 into updated guidance/models. Update .kb/guides/opencode.md and (if needed) .kb/models/opencode-session-lifecycle.md with late-Jan findings (auth confusion, TUI mode switching, context loading quirks, plugins interactions).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","domain":"kb-synthesis","estimated_minutes":120,"created_at":"2026-01-29T21:26:36.055908-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T21:32:24.957991-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T21:32:24.957991-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21038","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Synthesizing opencode/cli investigations since 2026-01-08 into kb guides/models","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:27:31.849053-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21038","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Read current opencode.md and model (done). 2. Find investigations since 2026-01-08 (262 found). 3. Filter for opencode/cli relevant topics (auth, TUI, context loading, plugins). 4. Update .kb/guides/opencode.md. 5. Update .kb/models/opencode-session-lifecycle.md if needed.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:28:01.117174-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21038","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Synthesizing 6 key investigations: auth confusion (env precedence), TUI mode switching (agent selection), native spawn support, plugin v2 API, context loading (instructions vs injection), binary resolution. Updating .kb/guides/opencode.md now.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:28:32.877961-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21038","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Synthesized 6 key late-Jan OpenCode investigations into .kb/guides/opencode.md and .kb/models/opencode-session-lifecycle.md. Updated: auth confusion (env precedence), TUI mode switching (agent selection), native spawn support (parentID hierarchy), plugin v2 API (function exports), context loading (instructions vs injection), binary resolution (unified pattern). References updated 24→30 investigations, last verified 2026-01-08→2026-01-29. Committed ac492883.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:31:58.642193-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21039","title":"Synthesize dashboard investigations into kb","description":"Refresh synthesis for dashboard: incorporate investigations since 2026-01-07 into updated guidance/models. Update .kb/guides/dashboard.md and any relevant models (.kb/models/dashboard-architecture.md, .kb/models/dashboard-agent-status.md) focusing on ops view/activity feed/review section/agent status correctness.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","domain":"kb-synthesis","estimated_minutes":120,"created_at":"2026-01-29T21:26:36.115167-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T21:32:24.106897-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T21:32:24.106897-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21039","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Synthesizing dashboard investigations since 2026-01-07 into guides and models","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:27:55.984907-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21039","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Synthesizing 24 dashboard investigations (Jan 7-29) into guides and models. Major changes: Decision Center/Strategic Center design, screenshot artifacts, tmux visibility, follow-orchestrator fixes.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:28:52.538465-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21039","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Updated dashboard guide with 24 new investigations (Jan 7-29). Major additions: Strategic Center/Decision Center design, screenshot artifacts, tmux visibility, follow-orchestrator fixes. Now updating dashboard architecture model.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:31:09.712744-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21039","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Synthesized 24 dashboard investigations (Jan 7-29) into kb. Updated dashboard guide, dashboard architecture model, and agent status model. Major additions: Strategic Center/Decision Center (action-oriented UX), screenshot artifacts, tmux visibility, follow-orchestrator multi-project filtering. Total 82+ investigations now synthesized.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:32:16.695357-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21040","title":"Synthesize orch status/frontier investigations into kb","description":"Refresh synthesis for orch status/frontier: incorporate investigations since 2026-01-08 into updated guidance/models. Update .kb/guides/status.md and tighten related models (e.g., .kb/models/decidability-graph.md) around frontier vs status disagreement, stuck agent reporting, decidability fields.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","domain":"kb-synthesis","estimated_minutes":120,"created_at":"2026-01-29T21:26:36.175998-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T21:32:25.818997-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T21:32:25.818997-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21040","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Investigation - Reviewed status.md (last updated 2026-01-08), decidability-graph.md (updated 2026-01-19), and identified 3 key investigations: frontier vs status disagreement, stuck agent reporting, and decidability field exposure. Moving to synthesis.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:28:48.975419-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21040","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Updated .kb/guides/status.md (added orch frontier vs status distinction, 4 new findings from Jan 2026) and .kb/models/decidability-graph.md (added frontier implementation details, stuck agent detection, decidability field exposure status). Synthesis complete.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:32:03.366639-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21041","title":"Synthesize sessions/handoff investigations into kb","description":"Refresh synthesis for sessions/handoff: incorporate investigations since 2026-01-15 into the session lifecycle model and any guides. Primary target: .kb/models/orchestrator-session-lifecycle.md; secondary: .kb/guides/orchestrator-session-management.md and .kb/guides/session-resume-protocol.md.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","domain":"kb-synthesis","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-01-29T21:26:36.240478-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T21:40:51.21289-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T21:38:27.09126-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21041","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Read investigations since 2026-01-15 related to sessions/handoff 2. Update .kb/models/orchestrator-session-lifecycle.md with new findings 3. Update .kb/guides/orchestrator-session-management.md if needed 4. Update .kb/guides/session-resume-protocol.md if needed","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:33:03.427195-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21041","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Planning complete. Major change: session handoff machinery removed 2026-01-19 (decision .kb/decisions/2026-01-19-remove-session-handoff-machinery.md). Updates needed: 1) Remove SESSION_HANDOFF.md refs, replace with SYNTHESIS.md 2) Remove session start/end commands 3) Add evolution section about removal 4) Deprecate session-resume-protocol.md guide","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:34:02.946224-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21041","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Synthesized 5+ investigations into kb models/guides. Updated orchestrator-session-lifecycle.md (Phase 7 + OpenCode inspection), orchestrator-session-management.md (SESSION_HANDOFF→SYNTHESIS), deprecated session-resume-protocol.md. Key finding: session handoff machinery removed Jan 2026, orchestrators now produce SYNTHESIS.md like workers. Commit: 6776be94","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:37:42.705106-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21042","title":"Synthesize spawn/contexts investigations into kb","description":"Refresh synthesis for spawn/contexts: incorporate investigations since 2026-01-21. Update .kb/guides/spawn.md and reconcile with models like .kb/models/context-injection.md and .kb/models/spawn-architecture.md (pre-spawn context gathering, gap gating, context-md template behavior).","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","domain":"kb-synthesis","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-01-29T21:26:36.303455-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T21:32:26.688957-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T21:32:26.688957-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21042","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Synthesizing spawn/contexts investigations into kb guides and models","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:28:32.927891-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21042","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Review investigations since 2026-01-21 (spawn, context) 2. Update .kb/guides/spawn.md with new findings 3. Reconcile with .kb/models/context-injection.md and spawn-architecture.md 4. Focus on: pre-spawn context gathering, gap gating, context-md template behavior","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:28:47.314121-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21042","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Investigation - Reviewed 4 investigations since 2026-01-21 (beads lookup, opencode-native, spawn-time bloat, reliability pattern). Reading context-injection and spawn-architecture models for reconciliation.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:28:58.030196-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21042","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Synthesizing 4 investigations into spawn.md updates: bloat detection (Jan 24), cross-project beads behavior (Jan 29), OpenCode integration depth (Jan 28), reliability patterns (Jan 22)","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:29:20.197721-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21042","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Synthesized 4 investigations (Jan 22-29) into spawn/contexts kb. Updated .kb/guides/spawn.md with bloat detection, cross-project beads behavior, OpenCode integration depth, and backend-dependent dedup. Reconciled with .kb/models/context-injection.md and spawn-architecture.md. Committed: ac492883","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:31:46.268395-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21043","title":"Synthesize SSE/HTTP investigations into kb (reconnection + connection pool)","description":"SSE/HTTP synthesis: close the loop on reconnection behavior and HTTP connection pool exhaustion. Consolidate findings since 2026-01-05 design doc + recent 2026-01-29 SSE reconnection investigation into a durable model/guide update (or addendum investigation) with verified behavior + recommended defaults.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","domain":"kb-synthesis","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-01-29T21:26:36.36526-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T21:34:14.972827-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T21:34:14.972827-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21043","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Synthesize SSE reconnection findings (2026-01-28 investigation), 2. Synthesize HTTP connection pool findings (2026-01-05 design + fix), 3. Update opencode.md guide with verified behavior + recommended defaults, 4. Commit changes","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:29:03.472209-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21043","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Adding SSE Connection Management section to opencode.md guide","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:29:18.60389-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21043","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Creating new model file to avoid race condition with parallel opencode.md updates (PID 91730)","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:31:14.644534-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21043","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Created .kb/models/sse-connection-management.md synthesizing SSE reconnection behavior (exponential backoff, conditional break fix) and HTTP/1.1 connection pool constraints (6-connection limit, agentlog opt-in workaround, HTTP/2 permanent fix). Includes verified behavior, recommended defaults, and success criteria. Committed in c4a2684c.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:33:45.821993-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21044","title":"Fix future-dated investigation filename (2027-01-27...)","description":"There is a future-dated investigation file: .kb/investigations/2026-01-27-inv-what-happened-dashboard-review-section.md. Verify intended date and rename to correct YYYY-MM-DD to avoid skewing recency/sorting; update any references if needed.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","domain":"kb-hygiene","estimated_minutes":15,"created_at":"2026-01-29T21:26:36.425322-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T21:40:51.265369-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T21:35:18.697064-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21044","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Fixing future-dated investigation filename (2027 → 2026)","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:33:14.554941-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21044","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Renaming file and updating references","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:33:47.195557-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21044","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Fixed future-dated investigation filename. Renamed 2027-01-27-inv-what-happened-dashboard-review-section.md to 2026-01-27 (correct date based on investigation content showing Jan 27, 2026 events). Updated date field in file and reference in .beads/issues.jsonl (orch-go-20967). Commit: d7e5da0e. Leave it Better: No kb quick entries needed - straightforward date typo fix with no learnings to externalize.","created_at":"2026-01-29T21:34:48.57202-08:00"}]}
