{"id":"orch-go-21047","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Audit OpenCode plugin architecture in orch-go: ...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:45:37.266325-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T09:51:30.45401-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T09:51:30.45401-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21047","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Starting audit of OpenCode plugin architecture, focusing on plugin loading, hook firing, and session injection","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:46:02.618355-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21047","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-30-inv-audit-opencode-plugin-architecture-orch.md","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:46:06.749503-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21047","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Audited all 9 OpenCode plugins, documented hooks/purposes/load order. Key finding: experimental.chat.system.transform DOES fire (702 events logged), custom agents use config-level permissions instead of runtime plugin gates. Investigation file: .kb/investigations/2026-01-30-inv-audit-opencode-plugin-architecture-orch.md","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:50:40.337361-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21048","title":"Disable decision gate in orch spawn","description":"Decision gate is too blunt - high false positive rate, blocks legitimate work. Disable checkDecisionConflicts() in spawn_validation.go. Mark 2026-01-28-decision-gate.md as superseded.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:48:44.306483-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T09:52:55.46298-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T09:52:55.46298-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21048","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Comment out checkDecisionConflicts() call in spawn flow 2. Mark 2026-01-28-decision-gate.md as superseded","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:49:44.574775-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21048","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Disabling decision gate check in spawn_cmd.go and marking decision as superseded","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:50:01.218389-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21048","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Self-Review - Verifying changes before commit","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:51:12.425439-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21048","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Decision gate disabled in spawn_cmd.go (checkDecisionConflicts commented out), 2026-01-28-decision-gate.md marked as superseded, --acknowledge-decision flag deprecated. Binary rebuilt and verified working.","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:51:38.4775-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21049","title":"Dashboard agent detail: hide tabs without content","description":"## Problem\n\nWhen clicking an agent in the dashboard to see details, tabs are shown even when empty:\n- SYNTHESIS tab shows for light-tier agents that don't have one (wastes a click)\n- SCREENSHOTS tab is almost always empty (never seen a screenshot rendered)\n\n## Desired Behavior\n\nOnly show tabs that have actual content:\n- Hide SYNTHESIS tab if no SYNTHESIS.md exists\n- Hide SCREENSHOTS tab if no screenshots captured\n- Default to first tab that HAS content (e.g., INVESTIGATION if no synthesis)\n\n## Location\n\nDashboard agent detail slide-out pane - likely in `web/src/lib/components/agent-detail/`","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:56:35.934908-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T10:03:18.795075-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T10:03:18.795075-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21049","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Dashboard agent detail tab visibility","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:57:33.828954-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21049","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Hide SYNTHESIS tab when no SYNTHESIS.md exists 2. Hide SCREENSHOTS tab when no screenshots captured 3. Default to first tab with content 4. Visual verification required (web/ change)","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:57:35.17481-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21049","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Modifying tab visibility logic in agent-detail-panel.svelte","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:59:28.200891-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21049","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Visual verification: Active agent shows Activity+Investigation tabs only. Completed agent shows Investigation tab only. Synthesis and Screenshots tabs correctly hidden when content absent.","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:02:26.374635-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21049","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Tabs now hidden when content absent: SYNTHESIS (no synthesis_content), INVESTIGATION (no investigation_content), SCREENSHOTS (no screenshots). Default to first available tab. Visual verification: active agent shows Activity+Investigation only, completed agent shows Investigation only.","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:02:55.522595-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21050","title":"orch status and dashboard not displaying model field for agents","description":"## Problem\n\nThe MODEL column in `orch status` shows `-` for all agents, and the dashboard also doesn't display the model. \n\n## Evidence\n\n```\nAGENTS\n  SRC BEADS ID           MODE     MODEL                STATUS   PHASE\n  O   orch-go-21047      opencode -                    running  Planning\n```\n\n## Questions\n\n1. Where does the model field come from? (OpenCode API? spawn config?)\n2. Is it captured at spawn time but not persisted?\n3. Is the OpenCode API returning model info?\n\n## Desired\n\n- MODEL column shows actual model (e.g., `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5`)\n- Dashboard agent cards show which model is being used","no_repro_reason":"Observed consistently in orch status output","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:56:53.537411-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T10:06:15.906199-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T10:06:15.906199-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21050","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating why MODEL column shows '-' in orch status and dashboard","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:57:44.736801-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21050","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Root cause identified: Model field not captured in AgentManifest at spawn time and not fetched from OpenCode messages API. Implementing fix.","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:59:03.158638-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21050","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Root cause: Model field was never captured in AgentManifest at spawn time and never fetched from OpenCode messages API. Fix: Added Model field to AgentManifest, populate it at spawn time from config, and fetch from messages API for active sessions. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/... ./pkg/opencode/... - all passing (pre-existing test failures in spawn package unrelated to this change). Verification: orch status now shows MODEL column with actual model names (opus-4.5, sonnet-4.5) instead of '-'.","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:05:48.544007-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21051","title":"Dashboard live activity feed: text rendering issues","description":"## Problem\n\nThe live activity feed in the dashboard agent detail has text rendering issues that make it hard to read:\n- Numbered lists appear inline instead of as actual lists\n- Missing newlines - text runs together\n- Other markdown/formatting not being rendered properly\n\n## Desired Behavior\n\n- Numbered lists render as actual lists (one item per line)\n- Newlines preserved from agent output\n- Basic markdown formatting (bold, code, lists) rendered correctly\n\n## Location\n\nDashboard agent detail activity feed - likely in `web/src/lib/components/agent-detail/activity-tab.svelte`","no_repro_reason":"Observed in dashboard while monitoring agents","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:58:32.846845-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T10:09:26.79352-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T10:09:26.79352-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21051","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Analyzing activity-tab.svelte for text rendering issues in live activity feed","created_at":"2026-01-30T09:59:06.392099-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21051","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Used existing MarkdownContent component to render text/reasoning events in activity feed. Now numbered lists render as actual lists, newlines are preserved, and basic markdown formatting works. Tests: npm run build - built in 12.37s, no errors.","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:08:29.592113-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21052","title":"Fix gpt_orchestrator bash permission patterns - commands without args denied","description":"## Problem\n\nThe bash permission patterns in gpt_orchestrator require space + arguments:\n```json\n\"orch *\": \"allow\"\n```\n\nThis means `orch` alone (no args) only matches `*` → denied.\n\n## Fix\n\nAdd patterns for commands without arguments:\n```json\n\"bash\": {\n  \"*\": \"deny\",\n  \"orch\": \"allow\",\n  \"orch *\": \"allow\",\n  \"bd\": \"allow\",\n  \"bd *\": \"allow\",\n  \"kb\": \"allow\",\n  \"kb *\": \"allow\",\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n## Location\n\n`.opencode/opencode.json` (currently) or `~/.config/opencode/agents/gpt_orchestrator.md` (after move)","no_repro_reason":"Discovered via permission pattern analysis","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:01:40.354464-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T10:04:45.116907-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T10:04:45.116907-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21052","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Fixed bash permission patterns in gpt_orchestrator config. Added patterns for bare commands (orch, bd, kb, git status, git log, git diff) alongside the existing patterns with arguments. Tests: JSON validation passed. Root cause: glob patterns like 'orch *' require at least one character after the space, so bare commands didn't match.","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:04:10.429775-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21053","title":"Move gpt_orchestrator agent to global OpenCode config","description":"## Problem\n\ngpt_orchestrator is defined in `.opencode/opencode.json` (orch-go only). Should be available across all orchestration-enabled repos.\n\n## Solution\n\nCreate `~/.config/opencode/agents/gpt_orchestrator.md` with:\n- Markdown frontmatter format (description, mode, model, temperature, maxSteps, permission)\n- System prompt in body\n- Same permission restrictions (deny edit/write, selective bash/read)\n\n## Benefit\n\n- Available in orch-go, orch-knowledge, and any other orch project\n- No duplication of config across repos\n- Easier to maintain single definition","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:01:47.285273-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T10:18:50.317032-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T10:18:50.317032-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21053","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Migrating gpt_orchestrator agent from project-local to global config","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:04:45.885706-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21053","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Create ~/.config/opencode/agents/gpt_orchestrator.md with frontmatter and prompt 2. Verify same permissions migrate (deny edit/write/notebookedit, selective bash/read) 3. Test config is accessible in orch-go","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:04:52.757418-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21053","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Creating ~/.config/opencode/agents/gpt_orchestrator.md with markdown frontmatter format","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:07:13.509804-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21053","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Testing - Verifying gpt_orchestrator agent is accessible from orch-go","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:07:31.834657-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21053","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Successfully moved gpt_orchestrator from .opencode/opencode.json to ~/.config/opencode/agents/gpt_orchestrator.md. Agent now available globally across all orch projects with identical permissions (deny edit/write/notebookedit, selective bash/read, external_directory access to ~/.kb/** and ~/.claude/**). Local config cleaned to eliminate duplication. Changes committed in b68b802c.","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:18:17.729856-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21054","title":"Fix gpt_orchestrator read permissions for global paths (~/.kb, ~/.claude)","description":"## Problem\n\ngpt_orchestrator can't read global knowledge files:\n- `~/.kb/principles.md` - global principles\n- `~/.claude/skills/**` - global skills\n\nCurrent read permission `.kb/**` only covers project-local `.kb/`, not `~/.kb/`.\n\n## Fix\n\nAdd external_directory permissions for global paths:\n```json\n\"permission\": {\n  \"external_directory\": {\n    \"~/.kb/**\": \"allow\",\n    \"~/.claude/**\": \"allow\"\n  },\n  \"read\": {\n    \"*\": \"deny\",\n    \"~/.kb/**\": \"allow\",\n    \"~/.claude/**\": \"allow\",\n    ...\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Evidence\n\nAgent session showed glob for `.kb/principles.md` returning \"No files found\" - principles live at `~/.kb/` not project `.kb/`","no_repro_reason":"Discovered via session transcript analysis","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:01:54.940646-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T10:07:20.293135-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T10:07:20.293135-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21054","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added external_directory and read permissions for global paths (~/.kb/**, ~/.claude/**) to gpt_orchestrator config. Root cause: relative path .kb/** only matched project-local files, not global ~/.kb/. Fix: Added external_directory permission block and expanded read patterns. Tests: go test ./... - pre-existing build failure in spawn package (unrelated to config change), JSON validated with python3.","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:06:41.565191-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21055","title":"Revise GPT orchestration policy: allow interactive GPT orchestrator-assist","description":"Update policy to reflect: GPT-5.2 is allowed only for interactive, human-in-the-loop orchestration assistance under strict tool gating; GPT remains disallowed for default/daemon orchestration.\\n\\nAcceptance:\\n- Create new decision (dated 2026-01-30) documenting the revised stance, explicitly scoping to interactive orchestrator-assist only.\\n- Update .kb/decisions/2026-01-21-gpt-unsuitable-for-orchestration.md to narrow/supersede where appropriate (keep disallowance for autonomous/daemon orchestration).\\n- Update .kb/guides/model-selection.md to reflect the nuanced allowance.\\n- Ensure blocks: frontmatter continues to prevent accidental make","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","domain":"model-selection","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-01-30T10:04:11.168473-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T10:15:17.576055-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T10:15:17.576055-08:00","labels":["skill:record-decision"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21055","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Reviewing current GPT policy and model selection guidance to prepare revision for interactive orchestrator-assist use case","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:05:41.208584-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21055","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Decision records updated, now revising model selection guide","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:07:21.191273-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21055","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Revised GPT-5.2 policy to allow interactive orchestrator-assist (human-in-loop) while blocking autonomous/daemon use. Created new decision (2026-01-30), updated existing decision with supersession reference, revised model-selection.md, verified block keywords remain in place. All changes committed (23b6cb55).","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:09:18.944125-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21056","title":"Architect review: update GPT orchestration decision without further patching old decision","description":"Completion gate blocked further edits to .kb/decisions/2026-01-21-gpt-unsuitable-for-orchestration.md due to decision patch limit. Need architect-level review and recommendation for how to represent new stance: allow GPT only for interactive orchestrator-assist (human-in-loop) under strict tool gating, while keeping GPT disallowed for default/daemon orchestration.\\n\\nDeliverable: short architect synthesis and a recommended decision structure (new decision superseding old vs split decision; how to adjust blocks keywords; which guides/models need updates).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","domain":"model-selection","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-01-30T10:09:55.639828-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T10:23:00.015966-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T10:23:00.015966-08:00","labels":["triage:ready","skill:architect"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21056","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Reviewing GPT decision patch history and model-selection guide","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:10:17.193-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21056","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Exploration - Reviewing existing implementation from commit 23b6cb55","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:10:55.65348-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21056","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Reviewing GPT orchestration decision structure and patch history","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:22:51.637175-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21056","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Review split decision approach (2026-01-21 + 2026-01-30) 2. Validate block keywords structure 3. Confirm guides/models are updated 4. Provide architect synthesis as completion gate override","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:23:30.799727-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21057","title":"orch status shows interactive orchestrator sessions as untracked agents","description":"## Problem\n\n`orch status` displays ALL OpenCode sessions, including interactive orchestrator sessions (human talking to Claude/GPT directly). These appear as 'untracked' agents, creating noise that makes it harder to see actual spawned agent work.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```\nAGENTS\n  O   ses_3f00ae9ccffe... opencode claude-opus-4-5      untracked* -            -\n  O   ses_3f27faf11ffe... opencode gpt5-latest          untracked -            -\n```\n\nThese are interactive sessions, not spawned agents.\n\n## Desired Behavior\n\n- Default `orch status` shows only tracked/spawned agents\n- Interactive sessions filtered out by default\n- `--all` flag includes everything (current behavior)\n- Or: separate section for 'Interactive Sessions' vs 'Agents'\n\n## Detection Heuristic\n\nSpawned agents have:\n- Beads ID tracking\n- Workspace in `.orch/workspace/`\n- SPAWN_CONTEXT.md\n\nInteractive sessions lack these markers.","no_repro_reason":"Observed in orch status output during normal use","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:18:06.294659-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T10:22:21.414311-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T10:22:21.414311-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21057","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating how orch status displays sessions and how to filter interactive sessions from spawned agents","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:19:10.061351-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21057","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Fix implemented: untracked sessions (interactive orchestrator sessions) now filtered by default in orch status. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/... -run 'Status|Untracked' - 29 passed, 0 failed","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:21:53.639074-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21058","title":"orch abandon leaves triage:ready label - daemon respawns abandoned work","description":"## Problem\n\n`orch abandon` resets issue status to `open` but doesn't remove `triage:ready` label. Daemon sees open + triage:ready and respawns the work.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```\norch abandon orch-go-21056 --reason \"...\"\n# Issue reset to open, but still has triage:ready\n# Daemon immediately respawns it\n```\n\n## Fix Options\n\n1. Remove `triage:ready` label on abandon\n2. Add `--close` flag to abandon that closes instead of reopening\n3. Add `triage:abandoned` label that daemon excludes\n\n## Recommendation\n\nOption 1 (remove label) - simplest fix. If work needs to be retried later, user can manually re-add `triage:ready`.\n\n## Location\n\n`cmd/orch/abandon_cmd.go` - after resetting beads status, also remove triage:ready label","no_repro_reason":"Observed when abandoning orch-go-21056","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:23:37.639713-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T10:25:33.412564-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T10:25:33.412564-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21058","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating abandon_cmd.go to understand how triage:ready label removal should be implemented","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:24:05.913309-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21058","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Fixed orch abandon to remove triage:ready label after resetting status to open. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch -run Abandon - PASS. Fix prevents daemon from respawning abandoned work. Users can re-queue with 'bd label \u003cid\u003e triage:ready' if needed.","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:25:18.303692-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21059","title":"orch complete auto-rebuilds on every call even when binary is current","description":"## Problem\n\nWhen completing multiple agents sequentially, each `orch complete` triggers a full Go rebuild (~10 seconds) even when the binary hasn't changed between calls.\n\n## Evidence\n\nCompleting 4 agents in a row:\n```\norch complete orch-go-21057  # rebuilds\norch complete orch-go-21054  # rebuilds again\norch complete orch-go-21053  # rebuilds again\norch complete orch-go-21051  # rebuilds again\n```\n\nEach rebuild takes ~10 seconds. Total wasted: ~40 seconds.\n\n## Desired Behavior\n\n- Check if binary is already current before rebuilding\n- Or: batch rebuilds when completing multiple agents\n- Or: only rebuild once per `orch complete` session\n\n## Location\n\n`cmd/orch/complete_cmd.go` - auto-rebuild logic","no_repro_reason":"Observed during batch completion of agents","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:27:10.489031-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T10:33:35.014087-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T10:33:35.014087-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21059","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Analyzing complete_cmd.go auto-rebuild logic to understand why rebuilds happen on every call","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:27:35.64497-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21059","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added isBinaryUpToDate() function that compares binary mtime against last Go commit timestamp. Modified rebuildGoProjectsIfNeeded() to skip rebuild when binary is already current. Tests: go build ./cmd/orch/ - success, go vet ./cmd/orch/ - success. Verified fix prevents redundant rebuilds via simulation.","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:30:35.007337-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21060","title":"Add batch cleanup for old untracked workspaces","description":"## Problem\n\n`orch review done` only completes agents with beads IDs. Old untracked workspaces (spawned with `--no-track` or before tracking existed) accumulate with no easy cleanup path.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```\norch review done orch-go\nCompleted: 1/1 agents\nAgents needing manual review (29):\n  - og-arch-bug-model-badges-18jan-edfa: missing beads ID\n  - og-arch-ci-implement-role-18jan-2086: missing beads ID\n  ... (27 more)\n```\n\n## Desired Behavior\n\nAdd a command to batch-cleanup old untracked workspaces:\n- `orch clean --untracked` - archive all untracked workspaces older than N days\n- Or: `orch review done --include-untracked` - complete untracked too\n- Or: `orch workspace prune --older-than 7d` - prune old workspaces\n\n## Location\n\n`cmd/orch/clean_cmd.go` or new `workspace` subcommand","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:27:27.132426-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T10:34:37.9418-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T10:34:37.9418-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21060","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Analyzing cleanup infrastructure and workspace tracking","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:28:31.598904-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21060","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Add --untracked flag to 'orch clean' to archive old untracked workspaces, 2. Follow existing cleanup patterns (report-only by default), 3. Consider extraction if adding significant code (clean_cmd.go already at 1037 lines)","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:28:49.77903-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21060","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Design - Found: Untracked workspaces identified by beads ID containing '-untracked-' or no beads ID. Plan: Add --untracked flag to clean_cmd.go following existing --stale pattern. Will archive untracked workspaces older than N days (default: 7).","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:29:21.170373-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21060","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Adding --untracked flag to clean_cmd.go to archive untracked workspaces older than N days (default: 7)","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:29:36.549336-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21060","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added --untracked flag to 'orch clean' to archive old untracked workspaces. Tested: Found 27 untracked workspaces (7-day threshold), 57 (1-day threshold). Follows existing cleanup patterns. All clean-related tests passing.","created_at":"2026-01-30T10:33:39.378859-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21061","title":"Architect skill references deprecated features.json instead of beads","description":"## Problem\n\nThe architect skill still references `.orch/features.json` in 9 places, but this was deprecated in favor of beads on Jan 4, 2026.\n\n## Locations to fix\n\nSource: `~/orch-knowledge/skills/src/worker/architect/SKILL.md`\n\nLines referencing features.json:\n- L215: \"update feature list\"\n- L283-303: \"Feature list review\" section\n- L308: git add command includes features.json\n- L405, L444, L470, L485: Various references\n\n## Fix Required\n\n1. Remove all references to `.orch/features.json`\n2. Replace with beads-based workflow (bd create, bd ready, bd update)\n3. Run `skillc deploy` to redeploy\n\n## References\n\n- Investigation: `.kb/investigations/2026-01-04-inv-orch-features-json-exist-tracking.md`","repro":"1. Spawn architect in specs-platform: orch spawn architect 'any task'\n2. Read SPAWN_CONTEXT.md line 951: references .orch/features.json\n3. Check specs-platform: ls .orch/features.json -\u003e file doesn't exist\n4. All work tracking uses beads, not features.json","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-30T11:24:42.887523-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T11:29:32.713268-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T11:29:32.713268-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21061","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Replaced all 9 features.json references in architect skill with beads workflow. Template updated, skill.yaml verification requirements updated, skillc deploy completed. Verified: grep -c 'features.json|feature list' returns 0 for template, skill.yaml, and deployed SKILL.md.","created_at":"2026-01-30T11:28:38.731377-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21062","title":"Scope: unactioned investigation recommendations","description":"## Question\n\nHow many .kb/investigations have 'Next:' steps that were never converted to beads issues? What patterns exist? What's the cost of this gap?\n\n## Context\n\nDiscovered that the Jan 4 investigation recommending features.json deprecation sat for 26 days with no follow-up issue created. The architect skill was never updated despite explicit 'Next: Update architect skill' recommendation.\n\nThis appears to be a systemic gap: investigations complete with recommendations but no mechanism ensures those recommendations become actionable work.\n\n## Scope\n\n1. Count investigations with unactioned Next steps (Next != None/N/A/Close/Complete)\n2. Categorize the types of recommendations (Update skill, Implement X, Create issue, etc.)\n3. Sample 5-10 to check if the work was actually done despite no issue\n4. Estimate cost: how much knowledge rot has occurred?\n\n## Output\n\nInvestigation file with:\n- Quantified scope (N investigations, M unactioned)\n- Pattern analysis (what kinds of Next steps get dropped)\n- Recommendations for process fix","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-30T11:28:43.998005-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T11:37:48.117805-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T11:37:48.117805-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21062","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Scoping unactioned investigation recommendations","created_at":"2026-01-30T11:29:09.215973-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21062","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-30-inv-scope-unactioned-investigation-recommendations.md","created_at":"2026-01-30T11:29:15.380773-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21062","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Scoped unactioned investigation recommendations: found 237 with actionable Next fields (155 from 2026), identified 5-10 high-value unactioned items (orch-hud.ts, usage caching, coaching improvements, semantic pattern matching, token telemetry). Investigation file: .kb/investigations/2026-01-30-inv-scope-unactioned-investigation-recommendations.md. Recommended two-track approach: (1) Create beads issues for high-value items, (2) Update investigation skill to require triage of recommendations.","created_at":"2026-01-30T11:37:18.21698-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21063","title":"orch complete auto-closes epic despite open child blockers","description":"Auto-closing epics causes inaccurate project status and forces manual reopen. Fix: before bd close on type=epic, check for any open blockers/children; if present, warn and skip closing (or require explicit flag to force close).","repro":"Create an epic with open child issues that block it, then run orch complete on the epic. Observed: epic closes even though blockers remain open. Expected: epic stays open or requires explicit override.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-30T11:38:58.516403-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T13:31:50.958496-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T13:31:50.958496-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21063","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating orch complete epic auto-close behavior","created_at":"2026-01-30T13:25:40.380962-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21063","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added epic protection guard in orch complete: blocks closing epics with open children, added --force-close-epic flag to override. Tests: go test ./pkg/verify/... ./pkg/beads/... - all tests pass. Smoke-tested with real epic orch-go-21068 with open child - guard correctly blocked completion until --force-close-epic used.","created_at":"2026-01-30T13:31:33.680552-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21064","title":"Update investigation template with Recommendation Authority field","description":"## Context\n\nPer decision .kb/decisions/2026-01-30-recommendation-authority-classification.md, investigation recommendations must specify authority level.\n\n## Change\n\nReplace the current `Promote to Decision: recommend-yes/no/unclear` field with:\n\n```markdown\n## Recommendation Authority\n\n| Recommendation | Authority | Rationale |\n|----------------|-----------|-----------|\n| [recommendation text] | implementation/architectural/strategic | [why this level] |\n```\n\n## Files to update\n\n- Investigation template in kb-cli (wherever templates live)\n- Possibly CLAUDE.md guidance for investigations\n\n## Success criteria\n\n- New investigations use Recommendation Authority field\n- Each recommendation is classified with rationale","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:06:14.741883-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T12:26:48.003188-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T12:26:48.003188-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21064","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Replace 'Promote to Decision' field in investigation template with Recommendation Authority table 2. Update kb-cli investigation template 3. Review/update CLAUDE.md guidance if needed 4. Ensure new investigations use authority classification with rationale","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:20:27.770144-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21064","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Updating INVESTIGATION.md template with Recommendation Authority field","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:21:47.652199-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21064","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Updated investigation template with Recommendation Authority field (implementation/architectural/strategic classification). Changes committed to orch-knowledge repo (commit 4e0a824). Template now includes authority table in Implementation Recommendations section and simplified Authority field in D.E.K.N. summary. Investigation skill reference docs and deployed files updated. New investigations will use authority classification with rationale.","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:25:58.041213-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21065","title":"Update architect skill with Question Generation phase","description":"## Context\n\nPer decision .kb/decisions/2026-01-30-recommendation-authority-classification.md, architects must produce explicit Question Generation output.\n\n## Change\n\nAdd Question Generation phase to architect skill between Fork Identification and Synthesis:\n\n```\nProblem Framing → Exploration → Fork Identification → QUESTION GENERATION → Synthesis → Externalization\n```\n\n### Phase guidance to add:\n\n**Question Generation Phase**\n\nFor each fork that cannot be navigated with substrate:\n1. Classify: Is this a Question (needs context) or Gate-level (needs Dylan's judgment)?\n2. Tag with authority: (implementation/architectural/strategic) and subtype: (factual/judgment/framing)\n3. Document what changes based on the answer\n\n**Output format:**\n\n```markdown\n## Blocking Questions\n\n\u003e **Hard cap: 3-7 questions maximum.**\n\n### Q1: [Question text]\n- **Authority:** implementation | architectural | strategic\n- **Subtype:** factual | judgment | framing  \n- **What changes based on answer:** [Impact on design]\n```\n\n## Files to update\n\n- ~/orch-knowledge/skills/src/worker/architect/SKILL.md\n- Run skillc deploy after changes\n\n## Success criteria\n\n- Architect skill documents Question Generation phase\n- Self-review checklist includes question generation verification\n- At least one architect session uses new protocol (dogfood)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:06:29.097374-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T12:23:42.963371-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T12:23:42.963371-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21065","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Adding Question Generation phase to architect skill per recommendation authority decision","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:20:43.636678-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21065","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Add Question Generation phase between Exploration and Synthesis 2. Document phase guidance with authority/subtype classification 3. Update self-review checklist to verify question generation 4. Deploy via skillc deploy 5. Success: dogfood in one architect session","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:21:01.916916-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21065","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added Question Generation phase to architect skill between Fork Identification and Synthesis. Updated phase numbering (5 phases total), added self-review checklist for question generation, deployed via skillc. Changes committed to orch-knowledge repo (e0b0d44).","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:23:20.591872-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21066","title":"Enhance kb reflect to surface recommendations by authority level","description":"## Context\n\nPer decision .kb/decisions/2026-01-30-recommendation-authority-classification.md, we need visibility into pending recommendations by authority level.\n\n## Change\n\nAdd `kb reflect --type investigation-authority` (or similar) to surface:\n- Investigations with unactioned recommendations\n- Grouped by authority level (implementation/architectural/strategic)\n- Show count and age\n\n## Example output\n\n```\nAuthority: strategic (3 pending - Dylan review needed)\n  - 2026-01-15: Should we adopt event sourcing? (15 days)\n  - 2026-01-20: Accept eventual consistency? (10 days)\n  - 2026-01-28: Deprecate features.json? (2 days)\n\nAuthority: architectural (7 pending - Orchestrator synthesis needed)\n  ...\n\nAuthority: implementation (12 pending - Can be resolved by workers)\n  ...\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Investigation template must have Recommendation Authority field (orch-go-21064)\n\n## Success criteria\n\n- `kb reflect` can surface recommendations by authority\n- Dylan can see strategic-level decisions requiring input","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-30T12:06:40.205489-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T15:22:25.309632-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T15:22:25.309632-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"orch-go-21066","depends_on_id":"orch-go-21064","type":"blocks","created_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"}],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21066","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Understanding kb reflect structure and investigation format","created_at":"2026-01-30T15:17:55.141607-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21066","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Add kb reflect --type investigation-authority command 2. Parse investigation files for recommendations 3. Group by authority level (implementation/architectural/strategic) 4. Display count and age of pending recommendations 5. Provide actionable output format","created_at":"2026-01-30T15:18:11.816308-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21066","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Adding investigation-authority type to kb reflect command","created_at":"2026-01-30T15:19:09.348181-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21066","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added investigation-authority type to kb reflect. Command parses 'Recommendation Authority:' field, groups by strategic/architectural/implementation, sorts by priority+age. Built and tested successfully. Depends on orch-go-21064 (template update) to populate authority field. Commit: a131c12","created_at":"2026-01-30T15:22:05.8217-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21067","title":"orch status: 100 all-untracked sessions 2.5x slower than mixed","repro":"Run: go test -bench=BenchmarkStatus_100Sessions_AllUntracked ./cmd/orch/ - Observe: 1323ms vs 530ms for mixed (2.5x slower). 500 untracked sessions are normal speed (514ms).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-30T13:01:38.098702-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-30T17:40:39.35106-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-30T17:40:39.35106-08:00","labels":["triage:review"]}
